reposted from @18millionrising -  today's the women's march! as asian americans, 18mr is proud to partner with @womensmarch to resist attacks on our communities. 
why do we march? to protest the deportation of refugees and undocumented people. for low-income immigrant families choosing between food stamps and a green card. for the disability community experiencing cuts to healthcare. for sex workers facing sesta/fosta. for families separated by the muslim ban, by child separation, by prison and border walls. for survivors saying #metoo. for black and brown people resisting police violence. for trans people facing erasure. for the land rights of indigenous people, and so many more reasons. we march for all of us.
.
.
🎨 art by @ana_piranha_ for @publication.q
.
.

text: today i walked in the womens march and i'm so in awe of the bravery of the speakers, my fellow protestors, and this amazing team i walked with. we must speak up; we will not go back. up until now, i've been hesitant to be too explicit about my identity and beliefs online. i was told to be afraid of what a potential employer might think when they see my social media. but i will no longer hide and be afraid. i am proud to be a feminist, bisexual, depressed survivor. if a potential employer (or anyone) doesn't support me because of that, i don't want to work with you anyway. #wewillnotgoback #womenswave #metoo

text:
i know that you won’t remember the march, but i hope that you will remember a few other things. i hope you will remember that the privilege of your life comes with the responsibility to speak up. i hope that you will not wait to see your gender, your nationality, your religion, or your sexual orientation targeted before you take action. i hope that you will recognize humanity in all of its forms and always see yourself in the struggles of others. i hope that you will be slow to accept barriers and quick take up burdens and carry banners. i hope you will spend your whole life marching.
i want to raise a fully informed child who will speak his mind when marginalized people are being targeted by the bully leading the government all the way down to the bully on the playground at school. 💕
ps. shoutout to my main squeeze for supporting absolutely everything i do. for having the same beliefs for our son that i do. 🍋  @womensmarch .
.
.
#imarchbecause #womensmarch #metoo #notmypresident #thefutureisfemale #togetherwestand #momlife #anythingyoucandoicandobleeding #womensmarchla #womensmarch2019💪

text:
i’m done drawing my ‘keeper of the heart.’ can’t wait to play with finishes once it is printed on wood. 
concept behind this drawing is how important it is to create our lives consciously, wrestle down the saboteurs, and empower the sage. 
thanks to some amazing coaching with mara vernon, i am creating the life of my dreams. 
the armored nature of the wings is born from the things i’ve felt a need to protect myself against and am finding my strength to expand in spite of.

i’ve sat in the discomfort this year of seeing how whiteness and feminism intersect and often oppress. following women of color, reading books on white fragility and intersectionality and leaning into new spaces have been important. and, i continue to hold space for non-binary thinking that two or more opposing truths can be true at the same time, which is why my girlfriends and i booked a flight and joined the women’s march in dc. non-dualistic thinking allows me to recognize that both palestinian and jewish lives matter. that both pro-life and pro-choice conversations are important. non-dualistic think allows me to be curious about people’s stories and choices that are different than mine. as i marched today i thought of the dozens of women who sat in my office this year sharing their own survival stories of rape, sexual harassment, domestic violence and torture and i yelled louder in response. racism, sexism, misogyny, ableism, homophobia, transphobia, islamaphobia and anti-semticism are embedded in american institutions—had enough of it?! yeah, #metoo. 👊🏻👊🏻👊🏻
.
.
.

#womensmarchdc2019 #persisterhood #stillirise #wholehearted #lethershareherstory #womenswave2019 #wimenswave #imwithher #ibelievewomen #womenaresacred

text:
april 4, 2018 will forever be a day that changed the trajectory of my future. ⠀
⠀
before then, i was a prisoner of my past. that day was the first time i shared publicly for the first time, i was a survivor of child sex abuse. ⠀
⠀
i’m not sure what i expected but i didn’t anticipate the wave of messages i received from supporters and fellow survivors. ⠀
⠀
since that time, i have focused my energy on helping more people begin the healing process.⠀
⠀
join us next saturday for the healing to end child sex abuse symposium because one thing i’ve learned is you can’t heal what you won’t reveal.  please tag a friend to help us get the word out about this event! #endchildsexabuse #youarenotalone #yourenotalone #metoo #metoomovement #whyididntreport.

text:
‼️ did you know that out of every 1,000 sexual assaults in canada:
33 are reported to police
29 are recorded as a crime
12 have charges laid
6 are prosecuted
3 lead to conviction
and 997 assailants walk free? 
today i marched for sexual assault survivors who were let down by the justice system. for sexual assault survivors who feel alone. for sexual assault survivors who fought the hard fight. today i marched for women’s rights. together we can persist for a better tomorrow for all women. ✊🏻 ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿
#99problemsandthisbitchisone #resistpersist #womensmarch #metoo #believesurvivors #timesup #womenswave

text: feeling revived, empowered, inspired, and assured to march with ~7,000 progressive voices in arizona today. this year, the march was riddled with unfortunate though much-needed fractioning and difficult yet crucial discussions, and i was a little hesitant to attend. however, i was thrilled to see native women, trans women, women of color, immigrants, muslim women, and alter-abled women centered as speakers and organizers of today's phoenix march. many spoke of the necessity of intersectionality within the women's march movement, within feminism, & within #metoo, and many speakers reminded us that women of color have been fighting these same fights for decades before us. a truly unforgettable day. thank you, phoenix - keep it up!! #knowyourherstory #noticewhoisntatthetable #womensmarch #phoenixwomensmarch

text: 3 years of #resisting the #fascist  government that we have today. a government that wants to spend billions of dollars for a wall, when #flintmichigan still doesn’t have clean water, when there is still homelessness, when there are families without food to put on their table, when individuals with different abilities cannot get the assistive devices they need to live, when thousands a day are dying because they do not have access to health care. i could go on.... this is why i march.  53% of white women voted for @realdonaldtrump . we simply cannot let that happen again. straight, white, and able women have to listen to our sisters of color, our trans sisters, our queer sisters, our sisters with different abilities, our immigrant sisters, our sisters who have been silenced, our sisters who have said #metoo, and our native sisters. we need to listen and ask how we can help. we need to use our voice when one of our friends/family/co-workers say something racist, homophobic, transphobic, etc. we have to show up. we have to be united. we have to #resist ✊🏼🏳️‍🌈✊🏿

text:
3/26 weeks of feminism is here!! “feminism seeks not to erase what is, but to add to it, lifting up the voices of those who do not fall within the narrow confines of the few categories offered by a heteropatriarchicalcaptitalist society. through feminism we can expand our vocabulary and broaden existing definitions so that more people are empowered to speak and understand their experiences. this understanding is essential for identifying what is problematic and taking action to achieve change and liberation for all. without a feminist vocabulary, oppressed peoples are defined in terms of negations: by what they lack in relation to the heterociswhite male. everyone (read: men, womxn, nonbinary folk, trans people, poc, etc.) deserves the chance to articulate who they are and what it is like to be them. the scope of our language determines the scope of our beliefs, actions, and interpretations. language gives rise to ideology, which lies at the basis of society and is the groundwork for political institutions which perpetuate existing power structures. without feminism, we are steeped in a language which privileges some and oppresses many. 
feminism acknowledges that many oppressed peoples are burdened by the daunting task of reconciling multiple experiences of self, many of which conflict and cause immense cognitive dissonance. feminism gave me anger. it said, “here, take this, use it. sadness is not the only female emotion.” i felt angry at my rapists, instead of feeling shameful, helpless and depressed. feminism granted me permission to say: “it’s not my fault” and “i didn’t deserve that, no matter what anyone tells me (implicitly or explicitly).” in a feminist world, i would be able to out my rapist and know that people would come to my defense if he sought revenge. i would have the peace of mind knowing that people know who he is and can protect themselves from experiencing what he did to me and many other women. feminism is the realization of everyone’s right to their own reality. through feminism, we create new discourses in which people tell their own stories and write their own narratives.”
name: Hana Hahn

text:
this month, three years ago i felt like i lost my innocence. i got this tattoo of a daisy not only to represent my favorite flower but to take back the innocence i felt like i lost. here is to the strength i have gained and the love i have recieved. 🌼

over the years, i have seen many people from my church, childhood friends and my parents friends post things like “it was her fault”, “why was she wearing that?” i just urge everyone  to rethink what you post because you never know who’s seeing it and listening. what you say right now tells other people in your life whether they can disclose their own experiences to you and ask for help. #metoo

text:
all 5’ 2” of me proudly carried this sign through the women’s march on washington this year (with frequent arm breaks 😉). although, no sign could possibly ever encompass every issue i am passionate about - it captures the bulk. 
i’m still angry about the 800,000 government workers who are not being paid. i’m still angry about how nc district - 09, my house district and maybe yours in charlotte or other areas in nc is the only unrepresented house district in the entire united states due to an investigation of criminal conduct and absentee voter fraud against the mark harris campaign. 
i understand a lot of you think marches are dumb or useless and that’s totally fine. one quote i’ve always posted in my room throughout my life is this: “our lives begin to end the day we stay silent about things that matter.” - mlk jr. 
on the days i ask myself why i even bother trying to get through to people, i think about that quote. it may not make a difference in changing minds but i hope all of you who have faced discrimination  because you’re gay, or have felt unwanted because you are an immigrant, or felt mistreated just because of the color of your skin understand that you have allies in this life - and we won’t stop fighting for you and telling people when they’re wrong. 
for further lighter inspiration, here’s my new favorite quote featured on a sign today, in reference to the government shutdown: “this shit is really fucking serious, bro.” -cardi b ❤️ #womenswave2019 #womensmarchdc #freedomplaza
name: Charmaine Feist

text: #womensmarch2019  you can now pre-order, "the me too movement of the bible," now @ https://www.amazon.com/dp/b07mtlv47w… on instagram click the link in the bio! #metoo #timesup #muterkelly #godsaystimesup my next book, "the me too movement of the bible." understanding the will of god through the word of god and the me too movement i had great hesitation in writing a book about the me too movement and the bible. in my hesitation, i begin to think that maybe a woman should write this book. in this book, i would be challenged to write about things that most preachers never preach or teach in their bible lessons. the sunday school lessons that are written never deal with the issue of sexual assault. most books that are written in the christian arena never deal with the issues that will be discussed in this book. i am about to write about something that if i came across in a movie, i would turn the movie off because i do not find such matters entertaining even in the world of make-believe movies.  but in dealing with these kinds of issues in real life you can't turn it off. you can't fast forward through the scenes that you don't like in real life. many who will read this book wish they could turn it off or fast forward through the pain. this book is a book written for all the silent victims of sexual harassment and sexual assault. i pray that god will use this book to heal all the hurt and the shame that surrounds these heinous crimes. coming spring 2019 ...take a look at dr. eaton's other books at amazon.com/author/revdrmichaeleaton

text:
washington, dc, 19 january 2019- the dc women’s march was a shining success on a dreary dc afternoon. today many hands joined together to hoist the lens of women’s empowerment in freedom plaza. it was a gift to see advocates of all backgrounds, beliefs, ages, and perspectives come together in the name of change, awareness, and pride. joy to free protest and the potential of the people! 
#washingtondc #womensmarch #metoo

text: 🇪🇸 por favor, evitemos que el dolor de una ruptura nos lleve a generalizaciones. no soy terapista ni psicólogo, sólo soy una sobreviviente de relaciones narcisistas familiares y de parejas, y hoy me parece muy importante pedir que seamos muy honestos con nosotros mismos, que busquemos ayuda de especialistas y estudiemos las diferentes características de los narcisistas antes de acusar a nuestras exparejas y exponerlos públicamente, porque de algún modo, eso también es violencia y abuso. somos humanos, tenemos diferentes caŕacteres, no hay relaciones perfectas y todos tenemos días no tan buenos que pueden llevar a desacuerdos y discusiones, sin que eso signifique que estemos relacionados con narcisistas. aprovechemos toda la información que recibimos a diario de las diferentes cuentas para aprender, entender y sanar, y no para lastimar o vengarnos de aquel nos lastimó. por favor, no generalicemos!. ❤ ✒: yo. 🇺🇸 please, let us avoid that the pain of a rupture leads us to generalizations. i am not a therapist or a psychologist, i am just a survivor of family and couple narcissistic relationships, and today it seems very important to ask that we be very honest with ourselves, that we seek help from specialists and study the different characteristics of narcissists before accusing our ex-partners and expose them publicly, because in a way, that is also violence and abuse. we are human, we have different characters, there are no perfect relationships and we all have not so good days that can lead to disagreements and discussions, without this meaning that we are related to narcissists. take advantage of all the information that we receive on a daily basis from the different accounts to learn, understand and heal, and not to hurt or take revenge on that one that hurt us. please, do not generalize! text:
thank-you so much for the unbelievable support we have received the last few days.

we are sorry the insecurities of a few people were vocal, but your counterpoints were amazing.

we’re sorry their toxic behaviors keep them from knowing how amazing we all are.
truth be told, we are their brothers and sisters, cops and soldiers, bartenders and clergy. we live next to them, hell we may even live with them.
we aren’t trying to ruin their lives, but the days of living as a lesser version of anyone are done.
we’ve stood together in the resistance, we supported one another in the #metoo movement, and we’ll continue our stance as we honor the history of stonewall50.

keep your spirits strong folks, we’re in the fight together.

#flannelfly66 #metoo #resist #stonewall50 #lgbtqpride

text:
solidarity. 
i’m so bummed to not be out on the streets with all today. and i know i’m like a broken record here but i find it so important—standing up for what you believe in—so, to those marching today who fight for the rights of others as hard as they do their own, thank you!! you are strong. and i am with you in spirit.
.
i stand with those women & allies who march knowing:
#blacklivesmatter
those who fight to #endracism 
to stop #policebrutality 
to dismantle a system built on profiting from #massincarceration
to #stopxenophobia 
to #createequality 
to establish equity
 and for all of those who know all too well—firsthand—#metoo
for women’s rights & choice & planned parenthood & sex education 
to #shutdownmisogyny
and #endthegovernmentshutdown 
i stand with those who work to #endsexism and #homophobia who #buildsafespaces and #protecttranslives
.
to all those who know #nohumanisillegal and that #migrationisnotacrime. what is going on at our borders, the separation of families, the inhumane treatment and the criminalization of immigrants is not to be tolerated. the act of separation itself is criminal—and racist.
.
we cannot settle into complacency or apathy. we cannot let what has become ‘normal’ in our society necessarily become equated with what is right. we need to first imagine and then work towards better—for all.
.
i am with you if you #buildbridgesnotwalls 
you of the bigger table theory. 
we must fight through #intersectionality and from a place of #lovenothate .

as we progress and move towards betterment—we must #thinkgloballyactlocally and #fightforothersrights as we do our own. there is no real ‘other’ — that is a construct, a sham.
.
we are all connected
.

there is so much work to be done. and we have to start with ourselves. make a practice of checking ourselves. listening more. and doing the work, speaking up in our own circles—families, friends, workplaces, neighborhoods, communities. having the hard conversations with our own men, boys, girls. in our everyday. it’s to us. every one of us.
.
#womensmarch2019
#womensmarchoakland
#womensmarchposter
.

power to the people. keep on.
.
#illustratorsoninstagram #womensmarchart #bayareaartist

text_retweet:
this a victory!!! god is good!! this is only the beginning!!! if you have not seen the docuseries #survivngrkelly then go see it!!! after i saw it i was angry with the system and angry that they failed one of my own kind...women!!! this is not about race or skin color anymore, this is about justice!!! i am very happy about this!!! #repost @officialmuterkelly with @get_repost
・・・
we did it!!! @rcarecords is finally dropping @rkelly from the label. thank you everyone that signed the @care2 and @colorofchange petitions, tagged and tweeted the record label and reached out via email and letters!  pressure burst pipes!
.
.
radio, streaming services and concerts up next!  we will no longer support businesses that profit off of and support the abusers of young women!
.
.
via @rollingstone: r. kelly and his label, #rca, will finally sever their ties after weeks of protests and pressure following the airing of the lifetime docuseries #survivingrkelly and years of sexual misconduct allegations against the singer. .
.
additionally, celebrities including john legend, lady gaga, chance the rapper, meek mill and jada pinkett smith have spoken out against kelly. #billboard first reported the news citing unnamed sources.
reps for rca and its parent company, sony, did not return rolling stone’s requests for comment immediately. a lawyer for #rkelly declined to comment. kelly’s name is no longer on rca’s website.
.
.
#muterkelly #endrapeculture #sexualabuse #metoo #timesup #trustblackwomen

“morda f*cking gow” 🐄 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
-
i really don’t understand why afghan media has recently taken a stroll down gossip lane, but that’s the dark side of entertainment and it’s slightly embarrassing. it’s embarrassing because we should be uplifting each other and rooting for the go getters; we have enough problems in our lives already.  i’m not saying everyone should agree with everyone, but if you don’t have anything nice to say, don’t say it. there’s a lot more important things we should be shining the light on: like how the taliban have been recruiting children, how salam maftoon found a doppelgänger by the name of @justinpjtrudeau, or how the #metoo movement has finally come across afghanistan’s women’s soccer team, allowing these strong resilient women to share their stories in hopes of preventing more cases. ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀
-

text:
little woman foi lançado em 1868 e traduzido em muitas línguas. permanece atual .
.

no romance, a guerra de secessão leva os homens ao combate .
. 
a mãe e as 4 filhas da família march experimentam a liberdade até então desconhecida: trabalhar, escrever, estudar música... sonhar .
. 
a mesma liberdade das mulheres nos eua e europa durante a 1ª guerra mundial. .
.

mas a guerra acaba - e elas são constrangidas a abandonar suas aspirações. o mundo deve voltar a ser exclusivo para homens .
.

siga @mulheresnosvertices e nossa coletânea sobre mulheres em posições de liderança .
.

text:
animals need our help 😔 rp @macielleslie @theresialovesallanimals @animaltruthandhope @theresialovesallanimals
@animaltruthandhope @meat_your_future. please watch until the end. like bulls used in bullfighting, this baby calf has a spear in his back, weakening his muscle strength and likely interfering with his range of motion/ability to move. notice how he frequently falls and sits.
.
he is stabbed, again and again, as the young bullfighter "practices."
.
can you imagine being a child and being attacked/stabbed like this, over and over until you finally die? not even our worst nightmares come close to the horrifying reality these confused, sweet animals face.
.
what a shameful sight. what an embarrassment to our species that we even “enjoy” these spectacles under the guise of "culture."
.
your reaction may be that of disgust, and rightfully so.  but, have you considered where your milk, leather, meat, and other animal products come from?
.
please know that, if you are still consuming those animal products, you are paying for something equally terrible to be imposed upon animals.
.
the animals we commoditize for things like meat, milk, leather, wool and fur, similarly suffer horror and pain, even though we may not witness it as clearly as the spectacle in this video. there is simply no way to turn a living, breathing animal into food or other products without immense suffering and violence.
.
actually, dairy in particular results in the killing of millions of baby male calves (some dairy calves, we imagine, may even be used for "practice stabbing" like in the video). this is because, in order to produce milk, cows must be continuously impregnated, and male calves are useless to the dairy industry and thus are discarded.
.

text:
am auzit răspunsul ăsta înainte, și înțeleg de unde vine. dacă ai fost sau ești în poziția "bărbaților" din această imagine, hai să analizăm un pic reacția ta: nedreptatea ce simți că ți se face pleacă de la faptul că, de obicei, nu e acceptabil din punct de vedere social ca un bărbat să lovească o femeie, dar nu se întâmplă la fel și vice versa. violența asupra bărbaților, din partea femeilor, există, e 100% reală dar nu e pedepsită, ba chiar e foarte acceptată.
hai să vedem un exemplu:
imaginează-ți o telenovelă spaniolă (un exemplu ciudat, știu, dar rămâi cu mine un minut). te uiți și la un moment dat, când tensiunea crește, ea îl jignește verbal, iar el îi dă o palmă. ea, foarte dramatic, se întoarce spre el și îi zice "plec." atunci își face bagajele și pleacă, iar majoritatea  spectatorilor sunt de acord cu ea. "bine faci, fato!","porcule animalule!", "nesimțitul, cum își permite!?"- sunt exclamații pe care le auzim din fața televizorului, și au 100% dreptate.
acum hai să ne imaginăm din nou scena. sunt față in față, se ceartă. tensiunea crește, el o jignește verbal, și ea îi dă o palmă. ce zice acum audiența? 
toată lumea e de acord cu ea! din nou! deși ea e cea care îi face rău lui. "bine faci, fato!","bravo!","mai dă-i una!"-auzim din audiență. dacă ar fi zis asta în prima situație prezentată, nu ar fi fost deloc ok. acum este. deci e acceptabil din punct de vedere social ca o femeie să hărțuiască un bărbat fizic, emoțional, sexual și să-i distrugă bunurile, fără ca acțiunile ei să aibă vreo consecință! 
și bărbații sunt victime zi de zi dar le zicem că au meritat-o, sau că nu e așa de rău. sună cunoscut?
.
dacă folosești acel răspuns pentru a argumenta că nu mai avem nevoie de feminism, nu ți-a ieșit. ai făcut fix pe invers.
ceea ce vrei tu să zici, are sens, e 100% valid, dar o formulezi în așa fel încât te opui singurei mișcări care încearcă să rezolve problema!
hai să milităm pentru drepturile noastre, hai s-o facem împreună.

text:
• la fabricación de un fiel y estilizado compañero de polietileno •

#puppy es un perrito diseñado para la colección #metoo de magis, compuesta por objetos de decoración y mobiliario creados por importantes diseñadores, específicamente para el mundo infantil.

este icono de la colección está basado en la mente de un niño que dibuja una mascota: formas esenciales y redondeadas que adquieren vida a través de un objeto amigable, resistente y colorista. 
su elaboración en polietileno moldeado en rotacional garantiza a su vez resistencia y ligereza, en un objeto pensado para compartir infinitos momentos de juego y de vida, en el interior y al aire libre. 
puppy se propone en los colores naranja, blanco, verde y dálmata y en tamaños distintos, todos pensados a la medida de los niños.

text:
💙✊💚✊🏻💛✊🏼🧡✊🏽💜✊🏾🖤✊🏿 today, along with so many other women and men all over the united states, i participated in the 3rd annual woman's march. 
as this being my first march, i was a little unsure what to expect. though the daytona march was small, it was a group filled with men and women of all ages wanting the same thing. 
equallity for all. healthcare for all. human rights for all.

love vs hate. 
towards the end of the march,  as my girlfriends and i were walking back, something happened. which was pretty much a slap in the face. 
on my drive home, i really took some time to reflect on exactly what happened. and contemplated whether or not i was going to share this experience. 
well, i decided that i will not be silent - because i matter, we matter, all humans matter. and we as a society need to stop these 'norms' from happening.

i will not censor my following statement, so please stop here if you are easily offended. i will not be quiet on this to make people comfortable. especially when the following vulgar statement was made with intent - to be uncomfortable. he knew he could catcall and get away with it.

this 20 something man was taught that this behavior was ok. and it is not! it is not ok, to drive past women and yell out of your window, "i would 'fuck' every one of you". this isnt the first time statements like this have been made to myself or others. but acts like these, need to stop. 
things like this are the exact reason, why marchs like these are happening. 
nevertheless, she persisted. 
#resist #wearethechange #whywemarch #wematter #metoo #myvoice #mybody #rise
#usingmyright #checkyourself #wecandobetter #womenswave #stopcatcalls #outthem

text:
“you are here to thrive you are here to lead you are here to do things that others don't have the courage to do and you are here to do them well.”
.
i really couldn't decide what image i wanted to use to honor everyone out there marching today. in 2017, what struck me about the #womensmarch in los angeles was the sheer volume of people and the peace i felt walking with such a large crowd. in 2018, marching with my infant child in tow was so fulfilling, and i witnessed many many women doing the same, marching alongside their children.
.
this year, in 2019, while i am not in the streets riding the #womenswave, i am marching in spirit, trying to create change through action, in this project, helping foster a community where we build each other up, offer support to women and mothers who need more day to day than we like to admit and a safe place to both celebrate and mourn. this picture sums up #whyimarch
.
the seeds of change take time to show any real progress, but i'm sure there are notable differences present between the march in 2019 compared to 2017. those in attendance around the world, what do you see?

rough times 
can a seemingly peaceful landscape be full of trouble? i imagine the tempest by turner and all the characters that could be in it. 
today was #womensmarch and i was reflecting on how the #metoo movement has affected the world. i was also reflecting on the fact that there are demonstrations over the macedonian issue and how a city can go from being relatively quiet to being loud and taken over by people. 
alas is change coming?

text:
women’s march in dc, 2017
.
seven of us drove in a van to the 2017 women’s march in dc. it was an utterly surreal, empowering, life changing weekend. it was the first time i‘d felt not alone in years. 
a few hours outside of dc, there was this two hour standstill at this toll — and every other car — in the sea of *thousands* of cars all around us — were women with women’s march posters, pink hats, whatever. everyone was cheering each other on and it was chilling and i cried. i had not felt so much support in years and years. i finally wasn’t alone. there are people out there that care — they care about *me*, they care about *women*, they care about all the humans in this country and people on this planet, and the hundreds of millions of them are willing to fight — for me, for you, for our future and the world. it was the first time i’d actually felt hope for my future in so many, many year. thank you so much for your love. we got this.
.
i love you @carmenmyersreed @yourpaldavidvevo @sklont @ericawhoo and kelsey and joyce 💗
.

text:
as a board member of @tacomaopera, one of my jobs is to share information about our upcoming performances that feature world-class talent in intimate theaters with very affordable ticket prices...how’d i do with my sales pitch? 😀

i am excited to share a video i found in association with tacoma opera’s next performance, benjamin britten’s 1946 opera, “the rape of lucretia”.
.
.
 https://youtu.be/bbevv8jpecek

first…yes…the title. although it is often described as one of the most beautiful modern chamber operas, “lucretia” is indeed a story from ancient rome (circa 590bc) in which a happily married noblewoman, lucretia, is raped by tarquinius, the son of an etruscan king. the crime and injustice is said to have prompted a rebellion that led to the overthrow of rome’s monarchy and ultimately to rome’s transition from a kingdom to a republic.
.
.
second…i am incredibly proud of the artistic team of tacoma opera who very boldly and intentionally chose to perform this opera in support of the #metoo movement. .
.
the video is from a 2015 performance of "lucretia" in england directed by fiona shaw (yes, that fiona shaw, who many know from the harry potter film series). shaw describes "lucretia" as: “a short story about a terrible night, but its really about the love between a husband and a wife, what it is to be in a marriage, and to have that marriage ripped apart.” .
.
.
even if you are not able to attend one of tacoma opera’s performances, i encourage you to watch the video to learn more about this beautiful modern opera that is incredibly timely given the challenges our society is facing today. 
#tacomaopera #opera #chamberopera #therapeoflucretia #fionashaw #benjaminbritten #tacoma #tacomaarts

text:
milhares de pessoas saem às ruas nos eua pelos direitos das mulheres
#notícias de hoje #notícias do brasil #noticias do brasil e do mundo #noticias do mundo dos famosos #noticias do mundo evangelico #noticias do mundo hoje r7 #noticias do mundo r7 #noticias internacionais de hoje
na véspera do aniversário da posse de donald trump, milhares de pessoas participaram neste sábado, nos estados unidos, de manifestações em defesa dos direitos das mulheres e contra o governo trump. desde cedo, centenas de pessoas se reuniam em torno da casa branca, onde a manifestação começou, às 15 horas. muitas mulheres usavam gorros rosa, um símbolo do movimento. são esperadas passeatas em outros pontos do país, principalmente em nova york e los angeles. em 2018, as passeatas reuniram mais de 500 mil pessoas, incentivadas pelos movimentos #metoo e time’s up, contra o assédio e a violência sexual. “o movimento começou como uma manifestação contra donald trump, mas, agora, é mais para que sejam reconhecidos os problemas que as mulheres enfrentam no mundo”, explicou à afp ann-carolyn, que participou das manifestações. em nova york, leah maguire, disse que participava da passeata “pelo futuro dos filhos e o seu. para kelly rosser, a marcha “representa tantas coisas contra as quais lutamos: a discriminação envolvendo as minorias, a política contra os imigrantes e refugiados e a marginalização da comunidade lgbt”. este ano, no entanto, a unidade do movimento sofreu fissuras, após acusações de antissemitismo contra vários de seus representantes, o que levou várias mulheres a se unirem à organização paralela march on, que marchava separadamente neste sábado.

text:
awlcrwanda2019 registration is now open at awlo.org/awlc/rwanda2019

at the last march’s women’s empowerment principles forum held by the united nations (where awlo was represented), the cruciality of women’s empowerment was the focus to attain year 2030 sustainable development goals.
for year 2019, as a member of the united nations global compact awlo is tailoring its goals towards women’s sustainable empowerment. hence, the theme for african women in leadership conference rwanda 2019 is ‘empowered for sustainability’.
.
african women in leadership conference holds this year at rwanda on 4th and 5th april 2019 at kigali marriott hotel.
.
african women in leadership conference is a meeting for strategies and capacity building to advance women's leadership. it engages key decision makers to generate solutions, implement best practices, and build partnerships  for women's development.
awlc mainly engages its first stakeholders - the women, to increase leadership participation. since effective strategies originate from women, through equipment for leadership positioning.

as the father of a young boy, i want  to teach our next generation of boys to become men who respect all women. .

text:
#10yearchallenge ✨
。
can you see a difference?
i can. a massive one.
。
me on the left, 2007:
+10kg, suffering from an eating disorder, depressed, not good enough, constantly wishing to change the shape of my nose, having problems focusing on any task, wishing to die, not looking in the camera, smiling forcefully😒
。
me on the right, 2018:
happy, confident, fierce, sure od my own assets, having a perfect nose (no operation needed😉), looking straight in the camera, loving myself the most😍😍😍
。
。
。
for me 10 year challenge isn’t about the looks.
it is about the massive positive change that happened in my mind🧘‍♀️
i have been studying western medicine and ancient medical traditions for more than 10 years now👩🏼‍⚕️💗
。
and with all that knowledge there is one thing and one thing only i would have said to my 10 years younger self:
。
start ｌｏｖｉ n ｇ  yourself❤️ now！
you are perfect exactly the way you are❤️
there’s no need to change anything in you but your own perception of yourself✨
once you love yourself this power will feed you every day and radiate to others🕊❤️🙏
you are a queen👸
。
。
。
i wouldn’t be where i am now if it weren’t for... ｍｅ❤️
i decided one day to stand up and to keep my head up.
i decided to face the deamons of the past.
i fought for myself and chose life❤️🥰✨
i was having love and support but i was at times blind to it... my family and friends were giving me lessons on how to develop my self appreciation every day, but it was me who had to do the homework💪💪💪
thank you🙏🙏🙏
。
and thanks to all the celebrities & friends who keep on inspiring me, especially to:
@chodakowskaewa @ivanmbart @ladygaga @jillianmercado  @siamusic @lenadunham @saramelotti_ @dodaqueen @fabianhochheimer 🙃
🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰
。
。
。

@mystryde  is a local, female run business in the north end neighborhood of boston. you don’t have to be a “runner” to feel welcome here. becca and every one of her instructors help bring out the runner in everyone who walks through the door. these bad ass women (looking at you, @race_with_rach ) have not only helped me get faster, they are the reason i love the run again. in the process, i’ve made some amazing new friends. cheers to three years, @mystryde ! text:
| actualité |
comment bien commencer 2019 ? prenez une marque connue pour ses pubs remplies de clichés et faites la déconstruire toutes les campagnes qu'elle avait pu mener avant ! 
avant @gillette c'était des pubs d'hommes version apollon 2.0 se rasant torse-nu dans leur salle de bain avant qu'une jeune femme vienne caresser sensuellement leur visage. 
aujourd'hui le slogan "the best a man can get" (ce qu'un homme peut avoir de mieux) est devenu "the best man can be" (le meilleur qu'un homme puisse être).
bizutage, harcèlement, mansplaining, la marque va même jusqu'à évoquer les nombreuses révélations dans le cadre de #metoo avant de montrer des hommes s'interposant dans chacune des situations. 
à cause de cette pub, gillette a dû faire face à des nombreuses critiques : des hommes appelant au boycott, d'autres se sentant pointés du doigt, indignés par la "leçon de moral" de la marque. comme quoi tout n'est pas encore gagné !

text:
#flommist @monica_artista
flashback to the women’s march sacramento 2018.
i made several signs and marched with latinx and indigenous women to the capital with hundreds of other groups from northern california.
✨🤘🏽💕⚡️
essay: #metoo
{tw: abuse, domestic violence}
the #metoo movement was one of the hot topics i was infuriating with. 
my mother was assaulted by my father...”he was such a nice” guy. her family members didn’t do anything out of fear for her and their own safety.
i was physically, emotionally, and verbally abused by my father up until i was 15. i came to school with bruises on my arms; my friends noticed and asked me who hurt me. when i told them it was my father, the first thing they said is that i needed to tell someone. we went to our school counselor, who immediately called the police, came to my school, and took photos of my bruises. 
my father denied beating me, and when i got home, i was threatened some more. he told me i was a liar, and he never hit me, (as he was hitting me). one time i blacked out, and he screamed at me until i woke up. he threatened me with lies that the givers would put my three younger brothers in foster homes and i would never see them again.
i hate that men (and women) control people with fear and hatred, i despise that we live in a society where men say “facts” and women speak their truth it’s say “fiction,” or we’re “crazy” or “desperate for attention.”
i tell my story so others won’t feel alone. you don’t have to feel alone, and like my middle school friends, we can get through this together.
my father was never arrested for these acts, and people were afraid to press charges. child protective services weren’t supportive of my case because why didn’t call before if this was occurring my whole life?
the answer: my father would probably have hospitalized me by then.
today i won’t be at the march. instead, i plan on donating money to weave sacramento so they continue to help women with children leave their abusive partners.
➖➖➖➖
may you feel empowered this weekend by whatever moves you.
and don’t forget, you’re not alone.
1-800-799-7233–national domestic violence hotline.
#womensmarch #womensmarchsacramento

text:
thank you, to all those out in the streets today standing against the oppression that exists in the world. i want to join you but i’m exhausted so here’s a sign of my support from home. i didn’t get a lot of sleep last night. after witnessing the backlash to the recent gillette ad asking men to be the best they can be, i engaged in a discussion around why some men are so upset.
.
according to jordan peterson, an influential psychologist, i’m just too sensitive, too agreeable and too passive and therefore deserve to be relegated to the inferior ranks of women and minorities. he (jordan’s preferred pronoun - please search his name and bill c-16 for further detail) believes, as do many of his followers, that men hold the most power because they are the most competent. it’s just natural selection. it’s evolution. masculine traits of aggressiveness and competitiveness are superior to feminine traits like agreeableness and compassion and these masculine traits are associated to power and leadership.
.
apparently, gillette asking men to encourage their sons to be empathetic, their daughters to be strong, and to model behaviour that shows respect for women and discourages violence against anyone is crossing a line. it seems that men don’t want to be lectured, at least not by a company that they are used to promoting a less progressive kind of masculinity.
.
according to at least one jordan peterson follower, it’s important to listen to his entire lecture and not just clips because those can be taken out of context. hence my lack of sleep.  you’ll need to get through over two hours of his talk called identity politics and the marxist lie of white privilege before you get to his dismissive take on intersectionality and his opinion that white privilege is really just majority privilege and, really, what’s the problem with that?
.
it’s interesting to observe that, in a culture so dominated by capitalist patriarchal thinking, an ad for razors could offer such a telling perspective on the state of equality.
.
now, off to the forest with me.
.
#feminist #whitefeminism #privilege #equality #dobetter #resistance #resilience #metoo #womensmarch #womenwhohike #hikebc

text:
when i was 15 i was raped by 2 men in their early 20s. i lived with this secret for many years. now i am stronger. now i don’t mind speaking out about my past. but what i do mind is when the younger brother (my former friend) of my rapist continues to try and connect with me through social media. i’ve blocked him, he contacts my family members and friends, and wants to talk to me. wtf leave me alone. i am strong but i don’t need this bullshit in my life. i’ve survived enough.
.
.
#leavemealone #survivor #metoo #notmychoicemyfirsttime #rapevictim #iwillsurvive #strong

text: der “women’s march” findet zur stunde zum dritten mal in washington statt. nach seiner amtseinführung anfang 2017 gingen am darauffolgenden tag millionen menschen auf die straße um gegen den neuen präsidenten trump und für frauenrechte, gleichberechtigung und toleranz zu demonstrieren. ihr markenzeichen: knallpinke, selbstgestrickt katzenmützen. auch dieses jahr ziehen sie bei naß-kalten wetter und bunten plakaten zu tausenden durch die stadt. sie singen zusammen, rufen: „not my president“ - und viele von ihnen sind auch drei jahre später noch wütend. sie alle hoffen auf nächstes jahr, 2020 und darauf, dass der in ihren augen beschämende präsident abgewählt wird und wieder jemand im amt ist, der sie stolz macht und ihre rechte, für die sie stehen,  endlich wieder vertritt. #womensmarch #womenswave

text:
consent before any kind of behavior that involves contact with another person is necessary. no, not a permission slip style “you may do x, y, z”. especially when it comes to intimacy, sensual touching, and sexual touching. without consent (uncoereced, sober, enthusiastic) its not sex - it’s rape. 
this photo series is illustrating that intimacy of any kind is not a reward for doing x,y, and z. because someone does a it does not mean they consent to b. consent once doesn’t mean consent forever - it can be revoked at any time as well. not respecting another person’s boundaries is not only wrong but when it comes to sexual intimacy, no consent means it’s assault. ~~
all credit to artist
~~

دوما براتون یک سوپرایز بزرگ دارم که دارم روش خیلی کار میکنم و فکر کنم شما هم دوستش داشته باشید بر حسب چیزهایی که این اواخر از شما بدست آوردم و تا چند وقت دیگه اگه همه چیز همونجوری که بخوام بره جلو داستان رو میفهمید. 😍
پس بریم ببینیم چه اتفاقی میافته...
.
.
.
.

text:
anyone who knows me know that i love food😁😁. i live for every treat, every piece of food that comes my way🤤😁
mum use to say that i would probably sell my own mother for a piece of food, and i wouldn't disagree😅😇
but even when those delicious treats are raining on my head i don't eat a single piece, because mum didn't say "værsågod" (means something like "ok, eat it" in norwegian).
no means no, even a dog understands that. 
but it seems like it is very difficult for some human males to understand that when it comes to human females🤔 why is that?🤔 are we dogs actually smarter than you after all?🤨
-

text:
new podcast with @tobinzivon! ep56: tobin zivon on authentic relating in the age of #metoo, open relating, polyamory and meeting a partner.
.
this podcast was per special request from those of you who wanted guidance or further talk about open relationships, polyamory and monogamy. tobin is my go-to for this as he has experimented and deeply lived with them at all.
.
what he shares:
.
some of the golden rules of healthy relating
the important ingredients to a flourishing relationship
how to reduce drama in your relationship, regardless of structure
his shift from ‘doing’ to ‘being’
.

what you’ll hear:
.
moving into authenticity and vulnerability to allow a genuine unfolding within a relationship
discerning when to be vulnerable and when to respect your communication boundaries
finding the living sweet spot of authenticity, vulnerability, and being transparent within each relationship
having ruthless self-awareness toward yourself and your conditioning
following the truth of your heart in your relationship structure
discovering alignment, or not, with your partner
ways to proceed with changes in your relationship dynamic
celebrating your partner in their fullness
healing your attachment styles, wounding, and imprints to have less drama in a relationship
expanding beyond the paradigm of dichotomy
showing up from a deeper conscious commitment to self, to source, and to each other
finding full comfort in who you are and what you want
living the fully embodied wholeness that you’re here to live
loosening your scripts while maintaining togetherness
finding a way to embody and transmit an experience of safety for you partner
being based in love and integrity, not in impulses of conditioning
recognizing the energetic shift post metoo, and embracing the role of initiator as a woman
meeting your partner at their emotional and communication belt levels
#magamamapodcast #healthyrelating #relationshipcatalyst

text:
..the biopic on the famous rbg, played by felicity jones..
how a young woman, managed to win the groundbreaking case before the u.s. court of appeals and overturn a century of gender discrimination. thumbs up!!!
in the stifling male culture of the 1950s, ’60s, and ’70s, she was asked to explain “why she feels qualified to take a slot away from a deserving man”. true story!!!
her famous quote we’re not asking you to change the country, we’re asking you to protect the right of the country to change.”
what a lady, a roaring lion 🦁. a real role model mrs ginsburg, you inspire us, you absolutely paved the way for so many women  we are in eternal gratitude to you . you have fought so many battles. volunteer lawyer for the american civil liberties union, advanced women’s rights & gender equality. support the #metoo movement, which encourages women to speak up about their experiences ..
and despite three cancers, ailing health you wowed to serve your country until you still have the strength to do it.. respect!!! 🌟#ruthginsberg#supremecourt#womenequality#genenderequality#womenrights#law#justice

text:
the questions
the thoughts
anxiety
the feeling of shame and dirt 
yet you see this but you don’t stop the questions 
you dig deeper into the wound and you try to find the root of the problem
but putting everything to the back of my mind until i’m ready to talk about it or even report it 
is how i cope, 
i appreciate you for your worry but i’ve dealt with this all alone in the past and i will continue to do this
because i’m all that i have 
no one else will help me or understand me except me
i hope you understand 
don’t look at me as a victim
i can tell the way your eyes water up when you ask me a question or listen to my answer
you see me and think “poor thing”
i don’t want to be a victim
i don’t even want to be anything -denise⛈

text:
flashback friday to the women’s march sacramento 2018.
i made several signs and marched with latinx and indigenous women to the capital with hundreds of other groups from northern california.
✨🤘🏽💕⚡️
essay: #metoo
{tw: abuse, domestic violence}
the #metoo movement was one of the hot topics i was infuriating with. 
my mother was assaulted by my father...”he was such a nice” guy. her family members didn’t do anything out of fear for her and their own safety.
i was physically, emotionally, and verbally abused by my father up until i was 15. i came to school with bruises on my arms; my friends noticed and asked me who hurt me. when i told them it was my father, the first thing they said is that i needed to tell someone. we went to our school counselor, who immediately called the police, came to my school, and took photos of my bruises. 
my father denied beating me, and when i got home, i was threatened some more. he told me i was a liar, and he never hit me, (as he was hitting me). one time i blacked out, and he screamed at me until i woke up. he threatened me with lies that the givers would put my three younger brothers in foster homes and i would never see them again.
i hate that men (and women) control people with fear and hatred, i despise that we live in a society where men say “facts” and women speak their truth it’s say “fiction,” or we’re “crazy” or “desperate for attention.”
i tell my story so others won’t feel alone. you don’t have to feel alone, and like my middle school friends, we can get through this together.
my father was never arrested for these acts, and people were afraid to press charges. child protective services weren’t supportive of my case because why didn’t call before if this was occurring my whole life?
the answer: my father would probably have hospitalized me by then.
today i won’t be at the march. instead, i plan on donating money to weave sacramento so they continue to help women with children leave their abusive partners.
➖➖➖➖
may you feel empowered this weekend by whatever moves you.
and don’t forget, you’re not alone.
1-800-799-7233–national domestic violence hotline.

text: although there was a low turnout this year, matt and i still felt we must march. every year i march for a different purpose. last year, it was to shine light on how much women are underrepresented in congress. this year, i march for all women and girls who have been victims of sexual violence and harassment. i march for black girls everywhere who’s voices are not being heard and stories are not being told. i march for survivors who were not believed when they tried to report their assault and for survivors who have yet to tell their stories out of fear of being called a liar. i believe dr. christine blasey ford. i still believe anita hill. i believe women and together, we will be the change. time is up on the old saying boys will be boys. men must be held accountable for their actions. i have so many good men in my life so i know men can do better. i believe in you just like how i believe in the so many amazing women who have come forward these past few years even if it means risking everything. we must do better. we can do better. #metoo #timesup

text:
the world is not equal, and that is not okay. women, men, and non-binary people are all equal and should have the same rights, but they don’t. lgbt+ and straight/cis people are all equal and should have equal rights, but they don’t. religious people and non-religious people are equal and should have equal rights, but they don’t. all races and nationalities are equal and should have equal rights, but they don’t. all people are equal and should have equal rights, but they don’t. 
this is a problem, even if you don’t see these issues in your daily life, it’s still there. 
sexual assault is a fucking felony but so many people treat it like it’s not a problem. 1 in 6 women, 1 in 7 children, and 1 in 33 men are raped. that’s not including other forms of sexual assault. 1 in 3 women will be sexually abused or assaulted while in college. that is not okay! for those who think that sexual assault is just a joke, unfollow me now. i was four when i was fingered at church. i wasn’t much older when my step grandpa attempted to do the same thing. i’ve been cat called and made uncomfortable and it’s not okay. 
excuses need to stop. if you sexually assault someone, you are a criminal and a pervert and deserve to go to prison for the rest of your life. clothe doesn’t say yes, silence doesn’t say yes, being drunk or high doesn’t say yes. you don’t do anything sexual to a person unless you have their verbal and sober consent. 
women aren’t weak, children aren’t dumb, muslims aren’t terrorist, hispanics aren’t druggies, gay people aren’t pedos. no stereotype is completely true, and you’re pathetic if you judge people based on stereotypes. 
trump is hurting the us for a stupid wall. i live in a town where most people are really poor and need food stamps, but they may not be able to get them for a month. their are people who aren’t getting the paycheck they need to support themselves and their families. america has become a fucking joke because we have a dumbass as our president. trump need to grow the fuck up and act his age, or go away. 
end of rant -

-
-

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

text:
i march because of girls like me who were assaulted and abused as a kid. i march because of all violence towards women. i march for females i know who were assaulted and the men walked without paying for it. i march for the females who had their voice taken away. i march because there’s a racist, raping, homophobic, psychopath in the white house. i march because the premier of ontario fucked over every student who relies on osap. i march because i care about the environment but the government doesn’t. i march because 50% of sexual assaults happen to girls under 16. i march for all women women who are fighting for equal rights/pay. i march for lgbt+ rights. i march because i work in an industry where women have always had to do double the work to prove themselves. i march for those who paved the way so i get to work in this industry. i march for the employees of the united states who are affected by a pointless government shutdown. i march because the united states needs gun control and if you don’t think so you can fuck right off. i march in hope of a future where i no longer have to protest. 
other reasons: -cuts worth $335 million a year to mental health programs. -attacks on people of different race, religion, skin colour, sexuality, etc. -minimum wage and sick day cuts. -cancellation of 758 renewable energy projects. -cancellation of indigenous curriculum. -failure of promised funding for rape crisis. -green energy act repealed. -cuts to toronto city council. 
so for those of you who attack me for being a feminist and activist, that says more about you than me. if you don’t think there’s a problem, you’re part of the problem. to clarify: i don’t hate men. being a feminist does not mean i hate men. but if that’s what you take from this then that’s a you problem. you have nothing to worry about if you’ve done nothing wrong.

text:
llego al año 2019 más ligera, con menos equipaje y mucho aprendizaje, sobre todo mucha introspección.
he sacudido el polvo de mi casa interna, la limpie con el perdón; primero a mí, luego a otros.
de confesión; la más dura y de liberación. confesarle a mi padre que #metoo. sí, así, cortito, en otro idioma pero con un dolor y desorden interno de años, de una autoestima destruida, y tantas otras que no se imaginan, las cuales han tenido sus secuelas y también su cura.

mi casa interna ha estado sucia y desordenada desde hace mucho, pintaba su fachada para simular su desastre, aparentar a través de la sonrisa que todo estaba bien. 
ahora, el lugar que habito es más feliz, en armonía, sin fingir estar bien afuera y quebrada por dentro.
con muchos sueños, miedos también pero con algo que siempre he sabido, que soy una mujer fuerte, valiente y de buen corazón. que abraza los buenos y los no tan buenos momentos. he aprendido hace tiempo a no preguntarme ¿por qué a mí? sino ¿qué tengo que aprender de esto?.
abrazo y suelto cada emoción cuando se va cerrando ciclos.

agradezco por todas las personas que han llegado a mi vida, las que salieron de ella y las que siguen, sin ellos no hubiese adquirido todo el aprendizaje que tengo, y voy por más. 💙🙌

text: don’t hold it in! let it go! shrug it off!laugh it off! finding that positive mindset where you no longer think negatively about others and embrace every person around you. i remember a friend said to me, ‘i keep away from my sister because she is negative about everyone and everything’ and i replied ‘you can’t always keep yourself away from negativity’ but instead try to help that person and encourage them to change their thought process. ‘if you love your sister, don’t push her away because then you’re thinking negatively’. family are important to many of us and won’t always think the same. i’ve finally got to that place where i don’t respond to those who feel the need to destroy me but instead spread my self love and body positivity all over the world 👌🏼❤️ photo by @beckydann glitter work by @gogetglitter #selflove #metoomovement #metoo #bodypositivity #mentalhealthawareness #confidentwomen @swimwear365

text: to dr. christine blasey-ford, who endured one of the most profound acts of bravery that i’ve ever witnessed: thank you. thank you for sharing your truth despite a shaking voice and the knowledge that in a nation that elected a sexual predator as potus, the outcome would likely be unchanged. thank you for risking *everything* to speak a truth you owed no one and for doing so in the most public and painful way i can imagine, while displaying fierce integrity and grace throughout. your unforgettable courage matters despite the outcome. in this #metoo era, we’ve seen time and again the domino effect that results when survivors break their silence. thank you for using your voice to speak on behalf of not only yourself, but an entire world of women whose stories of sexual violence echo yours in one way or another. thank you for trusting us to carry your pain with you and for making us all a little braver.

text: the queen is the most mobile, perhaps most powerful piece on the chess board. when you successfully show a pawn to the end of the other side, you’re seen as foolish if you don’t swap for a queen. but why is she, or why have we allowed her to be, so terrible (in the classical sense)? “the queen was originally the counsellor or prime minister or vizier (sanskrit mantri, persian farzīn, arabic firzān or firz)...” the vizier was originally a weaker piece. “...the fers changed into the queen over time... some surviving early medieval pieces depict the piece as a queen, and the word fers became grammatically feminized in several languages, for example “alferza” in spanish and “fierce” or “fierge” in french, before it was replaced with names such as reine or dame (lady)... more in comments! #itsnotchance #itschess #queen #women #powerfulwomen #fear #love #power #humanity #praise #loathing #past #present #future #ireneadler #metoo #think #patience #puzzle #havecourage #andbekind #blackandwhite #grey

text:
[ser mujer en #argentina]
en los primeros 17 días de 2019 en argentina se han registrado 9 #femicidios. a ese número hay que sumarle las desaparecidas: hoy se llama carla, ayer se llamaba agustina, mañana nadie sabe. y soy una mujer que vive en argentina, una ciudad donde la lucha #feminista atraviesa todo. paso el día observando mi lenguaje, mis puntos de vista, mis acciones, mi cuerpo, mi imagen, mis pasos y mis rutas. fíjense que no digo cuidar, me observo porque sigo entendiendo y pensando el papel de la mujer, el mío y el de todas, en este momento histórico que nos tocó habitar. 
más allá de los espacios de militancia o activismo, quisiera que pensemos en lo íntimo. en nuestras emociones, pensamientos y acciones como mujeres, hacia otras mujeres y de los hombres hacia las mujeres que tienen en su vida. 
no hablo de separarnos sino de unirnos, apoyarnos, re-pensamos y alzar la voz ante lo que vivimos. no podemos callarlo más. 
sepan, los hombres que nos acompañan que muchas veces tenemos miedo. que no somos exageradas ni paranoicas. [que estas cosas están pasando].
y mujeres, observarnos a nosotras nos ayuda a crecer. dejemos de mirar y criticar a las otras: hay infinitas maneras de ser mujer. que la sororidad no sea una palabra de moda: ¿qué tal hacerla cuerpo?acompañarnos, protegernos, apoyarnos y amarnos entre nosotras. esto también es apoyar la lucha.
y hablo de argentina porque ser mujer en #venezuela era otra cosa.
•
me encantaría leerles: ¿dónde están? ¿cómo está siendo ser mujer en sus ciudades? ¿cómo están viviendo los hombres este momento que habitamos? 👇
el vídeo es de @amnesty

#feminidades #metoo #nonoscallamosmás #amnistíainternacional

en los primeros 17 días de 2019 en argentina se han registrado 9  a ese número hay que sumarle las desaparecidas: hoy se llama carla, ayer se llamaba agustina, mañana nadie sabe. y soy una mujer que vive en argentina, una ciudad donde la lucha  atraviesa todo. paso el día observando mi lenguaje, mis puntos de vista, mis acciones, mi cuerpo, mi imagen, mis pasos y mis rutas. fíjense que no digo cuidar, me observo porque sigo entendiendo y pensando el papel de la mujer, el mío y el de todas, en este momento histórico que nos tocó habitar. 
más allá de los espacios de militancia o activismo, quisiera que pensemos en lo íntimo. en nuestras emociones, pensamientos y acciones como mujeres, hacia otras mujeres y de los hombres hacia las mujeres que tienen en su vida. 
no hablo de separarnos sino de unirnos, apoyarnos, re-pensamos y alzar la voz ante lo que vivimos. no podemos callarlo más. 
sepan, los hombres que nos acompañan que muchas veces tenemos miedo. que no somos exageradas ni paranoicas. [que estas cosas están pasando].
y mujeres, observarnos a nosotras nos ayuda a crecer. dejemos de mirar y criticar a las otras: hay infinitas maneras de ser mujer. que la sororidad no sea una palabra de moda: ¿qué tal hacerla cuerpo?acompañarnos, protegernos, apoyarnos y amarnos entre nosotras. esto también es apoyar la lucha.
y hablo de argentina porque ser mujer en  era otra cosa.
•
me encan notaría leerles: ¿dónde están? ¿cómo está siendo ser mujer en sus ciudades? ¿cómo están viviendo los hombres este momento que habitamos? 👇
el vídeo es de mnesty

text:
the women's march has been roiled in controversy since its inception, from initial concerns about a lack of diverse leadership to anti-semitism. still, hundreds of thousands are marching across north america and in sister marches around the world today because of a belief in a cause (or causes) that transcend the boundaries of the women's march as an organization.⁣
•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
started as a response to the election of donald trump and held the day after his inauguration, the 2017 women's march was the largest protest in the country's history, drawing 1% of the country's population to the streets. there were over 300 sister marches that took place simultaneously around the world in a show of solidarity.⁣
•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
the 2017 march was the spark for the mainstreaming of activism that has erupted over the past couple years, contributing to widespread participation in the #metoo, #timesup, and #neveragain movements. as such, those in attendance of women's marches this year are showing up in support of a wide variety of causes beyond just women's rights: climate action, solidarity with asylum-seekers and lgbtq rights are just some examples.⁣
•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
in canada, the cold snap hasn't stopped people from showing up in great numbers, supporting canadian-specific causes like the missing and murdered indigenous women and girls (mmiwg) movement.⁣
•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣•⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
#womensmarch2019 #mmiwg #cdnpoli #factsmatter #giveadamn #activism #lgbtqrights #transrights #climateaction
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

text:
silent lines
ucf art gallery january 10 – february 14, 2019

as society addresses and attempts to rectify the rampant sexism plaguing creative as well as commercial communities, social media provides a platform for survivors to voice their experiences. movements like #metoo and #timesup create community for the abused, and unity for advocating change. but not all experiences fit neatly into a tweet, and not all pain can be conveyed with a hashtag.

acknowledging the complexity of abuse empowers the art of yvette cummings arendt.  processing her own experiences and translating them into art, she encourages viewers to bring their own experiences to her work. her thoughtful handling of the shared pain creates an exchange that blurs the line between artist and viewer.... for the rest is the article go to our website in our bio. 
_______________________________________________________
adrienne h. lee of orlando is an art historian and a contributing writer for artscene press

text:
to the dedicated and responsible news agencies. thank you for informing the canadian public on issues that affect human rights and women’s rights. it’s important that freedom of speech of victims not be muted.
the recent articles of immigration of a criminal and a diplomat convicted of a sexual assault being bailed out by his government and fleeing. the most upsetting piece is pm trudeau inviting an international woman into canada to provide her protection. 
pm trudeau publicly admitted to his part of adding another woman to the #metoo campaign. he hasn’t serviced the tax paying canadian victims that are filling shelters in droves. there are victims still living with their abusers just waiting for space to open up. the oldest group of women of war are the caf victims of sadvr. they are still pows trying to live another day while protecting their children of rape. 
why isn’t pm trudeau looking after this group of victims. he isn’t prosecuting cafs pedophiles or perverts already identified by their victims. our cases aren’t being independently investigated. the military along side of our unjust system is only asking victims to step forward so that their evidence and medical files are placed under publication bans and gags orders while their rapist live freely.
we are canada’s oldest veterans. we spent our lives washing and ironing military uniforms and polishing boots all while crying from the chronic pain from the abuse we endured maybe hours before this.
our ptsd wasn’t brought on by one mere 6 mth tour but living as a pow on canadian soil 24/7, 365 days a year times the years under control.
where are our medals, parades and pensions. the war on military abused women is coming to a head. 
violet victim poppies depict our country’s true veterans 
the war on women that the geneviève convention doesn’t protect.
support the violet victim poppies on remembrance day.

text:
in order for the healing process to begin we must speak our truth. thank you for your continued prayers for the victims and the victims families. here are some brave ladies that have decided to come forward and make public statements in regards to their experience. we continue to shine the light on these injustices. a source claims that casey treat, and the leaders of christian faith center (the treat family), are supportive and working towards bringing pastor moses back from his leave of absence, to work at the church again. you understand how alarming this is for the victims. predators don't work in public. they are sneaky, cunning and deceptive. i hope the parents at christian faith school will stand up against allowing this man back on the campus of the church. please go to www.megachurchexploitation.com to follow along on the latest news of the lawsuit. 
i know it's hard to wrap your mind around this for some people. trust me, i know the struggle between loyalty and doing what is right. what if this was your daughter or wife? this is not a representation of the church that god had intended. this is not an isolated event. churches everywhere are being exposed. this is spiritual warfare against the spirit of pride, greed, celebrity, and fame. we stand firm and know that god is fighting this battle. his fight, his victory. ---
blessings,
janet russell
#christianfaith #abuse #pride  #speakyourtruth #hope #bethechange #bully #mystory #churchtoo #breakthesilence

text:
ayer leía, en @clarincom sobre “llegaste bien?” mensajes que se mandan para saber si llegaron bien, yo nunca le mande a un amigo ese mensaje, ni nunca me lo mando un amigo, pero si una amiga y siempre me hizo pensar que no era el miedo a que me pase algo a mi sino el miedo que sienten ellas a que alguien las aborde en una esquina y seas violadas o mucho mas, pero ese miedo es real, o infundado, viendo las estadísticas siento que es un estado del miedo siendo que en capital son 3 millones aprox y solo hayan muerto 136 personas y 15% sean mujeres y 85% sean hombres, si tomamos esos datos duros, me pregunto porque no sienten los hombres que si salen a la calle van a morir, verdad no los van a violar y no van a tener que vivir con la idea de que alguien ultrajo su cuerpo a un así no se mandan mensajes entre ellos y no revolucionan las redes con miedo a morir. puede ser que los varones no midan el peligro y no se den cuenta de las posibilidades de morir.
creo que el sistema esta planteado, para que haya un pánico y un sector de la sociedad se sienta presa en su propia burbuja, que pena que esto tengo que ser así y no se pueda ser libre en ambos sexos, los medios, las opiniones y los miedos ajenos nos influyen negativamente, empezamos a pensar por nosotros mismo y a sentir que el mundo a veces no es tan peligroso como creemos.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #metooargentina #niunamenos #miracomonosponemos #miedo #feminismo #machismo #muerte #violacion #buenosaires #caba #vivasnosqueremos #muertealmacho

text:
stop body shaming! 
no girl, no boy, nobody should be ashamed of their bodies! everyday social media and society is telling us how we are supposed to be and to look like. they try to push us into a thinking which we aren’t in control of anymore because so many things in our society implies that:
„you are too skinny“
„too curvy“
„too fat“
„your breast are too big“

but the only thing you should actually do is fall in love with yourself. show them that beauty has no standards and especially no size! it has no skin color no hight and no form! beauty is everywhere there is no limits and no definition for beauty itself! ♥️♥️ 📷:@yourwelcomeclub ————————————————— #everybodyisbeautiful #nudity #nobodyshaming #feminist #feminism #girlpower #mencanbefeminists #gay #lesbian #women #lgbt #feminismisunisex #fightsexism
#believewomen #womensreality #timesup #equality #love #feminista #standupforyourrights #metoo #iamanastywomen #sexism #beautyhasnosize #everydaysexism #tothegirls

text:
went to a march by myself: -for the times my best friends have been victims to assault/ rape.
-for the times guys have grabbed my ass and i pretended it never happened out of embarrassment.
-for the time i was assaulted at 16.
-for the many times my mom was assaulted because she didn’t know any english.
-for the time i was with someone physically abusive and let those memories be apart of the next relationship i had.
-for the time someone in my yoga class opened up about growing up being molested by her father and we cried together for her pain.
-for all the times girls are fearful in speaking up because things somehow end up being our fault.

i march for women. mothers. sisters. friends. trans. colored. blind. disabled. white. all. let’s ask the women around us today what they’ve been through and listen. i’m so proud to live in a country that is so progressive and allows us to use our voices. usa politics change the world. american women change the world 💕💟💓🚺👸🏻👸🏿👸🏽👸🏾👸🏼👩‍❤️‍👩👯‍♀️🌸

text:
people who eat darkness is a true story about a british girl who goes missing in tokyo. it's incredibly detailed, layered, complex, written in powerful prose. the storytelling ability of the author kept me fascinated from beginning to end. it's a compassionate study of lucies whole life, of her family, of other victims and the emotional aftermath of the tragedy. it takes a deep, hard look at the perpetrator and his childhood and life, trying to understand, without glorifying. the account of the investigation&search for lucie is riveting.the account of the court trials is mind boggling. all of this is intertwined with incredible insight and knowledge of japanese culture, the experience of being a foreigner in tokyo and the realities of working as a hostess. 
this story was especially chilling for me. i had a brush with similar hostess clubs, i met girls who worked as hostesses and i even tried working as one myself for a couple of days (and hated the experience) i was young, fascinated and fearless, i felt like nothing could possibly happen to me. but this is exactly what ended up being the demise of lucie. japan is a safe place, and it feels safe. walking alone at night as a woman is not a problem. men appear much more harmless, less intimidating, masculinity less aggressive and everyone seems bound by societal codes of conduct. to quote the author "the effect of this, for many foreigners, is to disable instincts of caution and suspicion that guide and protect them at home .conventional englishwomen would not have contemplated going to the apartment of a strange british man or working as a hostess in a london nightclub, in japan felt safe (to do that) japan was safe. and under its enchantment they made decisions that they would never have made anywhere else." it never occurred to me to think of it that way but reading thesewords, i realized it was exactly how i felt while briefly living in japan. i repeatedly put myself in very questionable situations, that i would never put myself in if it was my own country. it never crossed my mind to be weary of strangers, because this was japan, nothing would happen to me there. that, and being young lowered my guard down.

text:
there’s something so refreshing about dogs. why are they often so happy? is it because they have far fewer responsibilities weighing on their shoulders as we do? is it due to their lower cognitive ability compared to adult humans? is it because they live “a dog’s life” whereby everything they need is handed to them (quite literally) on a plate? partially, yes. but i think there is more to it. dogs possess an endearing optimism: that you will return home soon, that walkout time is just around the bend, that you will drop a crumb of food on the floor, that all people are kind and upfront. little things bring joy to dogs: fresh air, interaction, affection, food, water. it strikes me that we should mirror this appreciation for the small things. i have access to safe, clean water: great! i have food security: great! i have my freedom: great! i have friends, family, and the ability to connect with people: fantastic! not only do dogs bring us joy and companionship, they teach us that appreciating the simplicities of life and reassessing our values can go a long way in aiding our happiness and fulfilment. ~copingdiary
~
~
~

.
their “value” is inextricably linked to their virginity status meaning their “worth” decreases with every sexual encounter, making them less marketable.
.
having sex before marriage deprives their fathers of the joy of “giving away” a “clean,” “unused,” and “undamaged” daughter.
.
sex needs to be as pleasurable as possible for their future husbands, which is why they need to abstain from sex until marriage.
.
to dress modestly in order to keep men from committing the sin of lust.

it’s unnatural for women to have sexual desires.” 🥀🥀🥀link in bio🥀🥀🥀

text:
oh. em. gee. i almost forgot what today is!!!
so on this day, annually, i celebrate as if it were my new years day as it marks the anniversary of the day i had my stroke-(this year marks 9 years). i woke up with a tingling in my face which turned into drooping and by the time i reached the hospital i couldn't feel the left side of my body. the doctors attributed this to a caustic amount of stress in my life that caused abnormally high blood pressure which forced a teeny clot through what should have been a benign hole in my heart. i spent 10 days in the hospital and several months in bed/pt. take it from me... no one is worth this much stress! 
loves, make a choice to be happy. this was my catalyst and my life is certainly tenfold happier now. 🙂 💗
i am celebrating tonight. have a drink with me and be happy you are alive. cheers y'all!! 🍷🍻🥂🍺🍾
