lugar: teatro ángela peralta
📆 19 de enero
🕡 7:00 pm
📍foro de la casa de la cultura, mesones #71.
🎫 entrada: donación voluntaria

caminos, es un proyecto artí­stico y social cuyo objetivo es ser un performance que involucra dos tipos de arte, la danza y el canto. es un discurso que protesta contra la segregación de todo aquello que es diferente o no cumple con los estereotipos sociales. muestra una realidad: la discriminación en distintos ámbitos que se vive en nuestro país (méxico) y se ignora por la cotidianidad.

#soycaminos #caminos #ourway #myway #metoo san miguel de allende

text:
happier times. 
as we spend with our mom what are likely her last weeks of earthly life, i am overwhelmed with grief, frustration, confusion, adoration, denial, pride, hope, anger, fear, exhaustion. an endless list.
fluid feelings.
floods of emotion fill my days and dreams.  during conversations i look people in the eyes, but my mind meanders elsewhere. 
it turns out, the happiness in this photo was largely an illusion.
my mom and a few other people harbored a horrible secret. 
during the season the photographer snapped this photo, my mom survived an egregious attack. decades later that event would upend and reshape the lives of dozens more innocent people. the thought of that aggressive and selfish act pierces my heart every day. i accept it happened, but i will never get over it.
a silver lining looms though. i’m certain my mom’s headed to a better place and i find giddy joy in knowing her pain will end there.
i’ve reflected on amazing moments together, like watching her round on the cops hand-signaling her to stop so they could ticket her for speeding. or the time she made a mud slide in the front yard for my brother and me. my mom and i danced like nobody was watching and we shared some magnificent meals and milestones.
it hurts deeply to watch my mom live with so much mental and physical pain, but i’ve seen her strength in action, so i believe it’s a part of her soul even if it’s not evident in her body. 
she’s tougher than nails, having survived cancer and countless disappointments. the hardest obstacle she said she’d ever endured was the loss of a child.
during the 1970s, my mom birthed a stillborn baby. eleven months later, she visited her other two babies in the hospital at the same time (the oldest having suffered multiple seizures and the youngest a premature newborn).
when i was young these challenges didn’t phase me much. now, as a mother, i can’t imagine what that year must have felt like for her in real-time.
my mom’s scared about death but thrilled she will finally cradle her tiny baby again soon. that makes me smile.
i pray no matter how many days this warrior has left here comfort and peace overpower her pain.
#hospice #caregiver #pray #metoo

text:
ok @vivid_winner #pizzagate #pedogate #pedovore

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
you have a voice.
it can be loud. it can be quiet. it can be sweet and dust your lips like powdered sugar. it can be harsh and cut your mouth as broken shards of glass fall out of your mouth. what do you want to say? taking your voice into your hands and making something. something that speaks for you. a visual representation of your truth. what colour are you? smearing your truth all over the landscape to reveal parts unknown and secrets unseen. give your voice its place to be heard. through your fingers or your toes. expose different parts of yourself to yourself. and share it. show it. scream it. whisper it. say it with colour smears and glue. pencil and feathers. light and dark. 
you have a voice. we want to see it. 
expose your exposure.
.
.
for more info and signing up please check our link in bio or email womensartshow15@gmail.com .
.
.

text:
this is my bitch face. my fed-up face. it's the wake of my first women's march, and snow or shine i am all there. because the wild woman in me has woken and is ready to do my part in raising up the feminine. 
alan watts wrote a book about the pulls of a man between spirit and nature. spirit is the masculine, and nature the feminine. that a man chooses between devoting his life wholly to god and spirit, or falling in submission to his feminine parts. this view is extreme and i do not adhere to it completely, but it brings up this interesting notion of a choice. he never questioned the natural instinct of a woman, but saw a choice for men to embrace their feminine parts in support of those they love, and learning to control aggression. i thank all men who embrace and/or support the feminine with an open mind. as always, some words to share:

may you let your feelings be tools of cognition.
instincts were first of nature, and the natural feminine in you holds the inner-truth of what you feel.
we are wild at our cores, but not in a way that is deemed vicious.
wild like the moon, feminine energy has us dance as a community around it.
as one with no sections of poorer worth or ability.
because the feminine is mysterious to the masculine is never a grounds to control the feminine.
if you say "no" to the future of the divine feminine, we have no obligation to adhere to that cry, for we have been criticized in saying "no" to the masculine control of our sex.
i see a world in which aggression may perish, and we all rise as one, embracing the feminine parts of us all.
where both sides to a story are heard and accepted.
where society holds true victims in a greater state of need than the falsely accused.
where those falsely accused digress from violence towards femininity, because we do hear you as long as you do not drag us down with anger.
where voices crying "metoo" are not criticized for latency, and are instead met with open arms of communal healing.
a world where we live not in fear.

ps: i don't like you very much, trump.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i've seen this going around for a few things lately.... trauma, assault and eating disorders mostly. and it always strikes me because i've experienced all three of those and with them, it is really f*ing hard to take responsibility. ⠀
.⠀
for me, the eating disorder was my way of coping with the assault, but i didn't realize this until many years later. and even still, it can be hard to grasp this concept. it seems so unfair right? like, 15 years of my life have been taken away because of someone else's horrible decisions. and what, he just walks away unbothered, not ever knowing i've suffered a day in my life from him? why is this my responsibility!? i get those thoughts. you’re not alone.⠀
.⠀
even though people were there for me. so many people helped with therapy bills, hospital bills, driving me places, medicine costs, my uncontrollable crying and panic attacks, my extreme fears and anxiety. people supported and never gave up on me.⠀
.⠀
but here's the thing.... no one can make me better. no one can do the work for me. as much as everyone so selflessly gave and did for me, it was (is) ultimately up to me to make a change. when i was able to begin taking responsibility for my own health and happiness, i began to see change. ⠀
.⠀
what happened to me will never be my fault, but healing and moving on and taking control of my self and life will always be my responsibility. a very hard concept for me... and many others i'm realizing. but we can do this. you can do this. i believe in you -- because i didn't believe in myself and here i am... proof that healing is possible.⠀
.⠀
sending you love and hugs. be gentle with yourself. you’re not alone ❤✨🌈
.

for me, the eating disorder was my way of coping with the assault, but i didn't realize this until many years later. and even still, it can be hard to grasp this concept. it seems so unfair right? like, 15 years of my life have been taken away because of someone else's horrible decisions. and what, he just walks away unbothered, not ever knowing i have suffered a day in my life from him? why is this my responsibility!? i get those thoughts. you’re not alone.⠀
.⠀
even though people were there for me. so many people helped with therapy bills, hospital bills, driving me places, medicine costs, my uncontrollable crying and panic attacks, my extreme fears and anxiety. people suppoed and never gave up on me.⠀
.⠀
but here's the thing.... no one can make me better. no one can do the work for me. as much as everyone so selflessly gave and did for me, it was (is) ultimately up to me to make a change. when i was able to begin taking responsibility for my own health and happiness, i began to see change. ⠀
.⠀
what happened to me will never be my fault, but healing and moving on and taking control of my self and life will always be my responsibility. a very hard concept for me... and many others i am realizing. but we can do this. you can do this. i believe in you -- because i didn't believe in myself and here i am... proof that healing is possible.⠀
.⠀
sending you love and hugs. be gentle with yourself. you’re not alone ❤✨🌈

text:
this weekend marks the third anniversary of the women’s march. it has been an amazing journey to watch the impact this organized march has had on communities and our country. this year, sadly, i have to sit this one out. however, that does not change my solidarity with the concept of what this march means to so many women, men, children, and communities. i’ll be with you all in spirit. thank you for marching for me and others.⠀
⠀
we encourage you to always speak your mind and remind you that you have the absolute right to use your voice in protest! these marches tend to be peaceful, but i acknowledge that times are rough. topics such as immigration, child-parent separation at the border, and the #metoo movement are at the core for a lot of people this year. these things can become emotional.⠀
⠀
we want to help you out with some protesting tips. know your rights when you hit those streets today. check out our stories for tips from the @aclu_nationwide on your rights and actions as a protester. ⠀
⠀
sending love, strength, and good vibes!

text:
“we come in peace.  but we mean business.” we have been fighting for equality for generations - advocating for change.  little by little we have scored victories.  my mom’s generation fought for our right to be in the work place, to be paid equally, to be treated as human beings deserving of respect for our space and bodies.  thank you, arleen labella, joy leach, bette george (just to name a few), for your role in pushing this movement forward. 
let’s be the last generation that has to deal with gender inequality.  deep in our hearts we all know it’s wrong.  let’s do something about it!

this is for you if...
💎you've been struggling to let go of the hurt from 2018 💎you've been struggling with old relationship drama, family stuff 💎you've been holding yourself hostage to not so great decisions or choices you had to make 💎you've been feeling the emotional baggage you are dragging around getting heavier and feel like you're suffocating 💎the #metoo and #silencerkelly movements have brought the pain of your past back to the forefront of your mind

i will not be posting the link publicly, so please pm me if you want to join us and i will provide you with it. :)

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
carta de despedida: 
abuela, mamá, hermanas, amigas, compañeras, me dirijo a vosotras porque lo vais a entender mejor. vosotras también tenéis miedo de salir un día y no volver. sentís pánico de que si un día no volvéis la justicia no os haga justicia. 
quería escribir esta carta advirtiendo que si un día no vuelvo, no ha sido elección mía. yo jamás me marcharía sin avisar. os lo prometo, confiad en mí.

si algún día desaparezco y no vuelvo seguramente esté muerta y (en el mejor de los casos) encontrareis mi cuerpo, porque hay muchas personas que no han podido enterrar a las victimas porque jamás se ha vuelto a saber de ellas.

en ese caso, o mientras me encontráis, os suplico que hagáis oídos sordos a todo lo que digan sobre mí. yo tengo claro y vosotros también, que siempre he intentado ser la mejor persona que podía ser. 
la única “culpa” que podrán echarme (y lo harán) es la de querer ser una mujer libre. 
como muchos sabéis, no me duermo si no tengo la conciencia tranquila. por lo que me siento orgullosa de todo lo que he hecho. y siempre que me equivoque (espero hacerlo) rectificaré y pediré perdón. lo que no haré nunca es lamentarme ni pedir perdón por ser una mujer libre, porque es mi derecho y gran parte de mi vida está focalizada en conseguir que otras mujeres se empoderen y se sientan libres como yo. 
seguramente mostrarán mis redes sociales intentando justificar “que me lo he buscado” o insinuando que soy una zorra, una puta, una buscona, una libertina, o mil calificativos que utilizarán para manchar mi nombre. 
también dirán que “no tenia que haber salido sola”, que “estaba provocando”, hablaran de qué ropa llevaba puesta, con quién me relacionaba.

mejor no escuchéis, porque en este sistema patriarcal siempre se busca culpabilizar a la víctima, como han hecho con tantas anteriores y muchas habéis llegado a dudar. por favor, no lo hagáis, no dudéis de mí.

nada justifica que no vuelva, porque yo no elegí irme, fue culpa del patriarcado. .
.
.
***si eres mujer te invito a que compartas esta carta o hagas la tuya propia pero necesitamos que nos tomen en serio. nunca sabemos quién va a ser la próxima. y sí, vivimos con puto miedo.

text: one of the best parts of my new gig is teaming up with a female-owned manufacturing partner in asia. the team supporting my project is full of spirited women and respectful men. it’s surprising how less draining these nightly conference calls are and how much more i want to work when i don’t have to worry about being heard, having my thoughts taken seriously, or needing to constantly prove i’m competent at my job. one day silicon valley will catch up. 👩🏼‍💻👨🏽‍💻👩🏻‍💻👨🏾‍💻#womensupportingwomen #mensupportingwomen #dogssupportingwomen

text:
people try to help by giving me advice on how to get better often. i appreciate they mean well. however, i will never be better in the way they think as for someone like me it's so deep rooted it will always be part of me. i can learn to live with it, love myself and create a life of meaning. it will always be there though and have an effect on the decisions i make. healing for me is not getting better it is taming my demons so i'm in control of them. here is to my healing process as in 10-12 months time i go through therapy for the first time since i was 15 (31 now) based on sexual assault/childhood abuse (not growing up with domestic violence). to people trying to heal from #cptsd you can do this your not alone xx

text:
: સ્વરાનું સેક્સ્યુઅલ હેરેસમેન્ટ થયું હતું!
કોઈનું નામ લીધા વિના સ્વરાએ કહ્યું હતું કે, ‘હેરેસમેન્ટ વર્કપ્લેસ પર થયું હતું અને એ ડિરેક્ટર ‘હવસખોર’ હતો. મને એનો ખ્યાલ આવતાં છથી આઠ વર્ષ લાગ્યા હતા. આવા પ્રકારની પેનલ ડિસ્કશનમાં બીજા કોઈએ હેરેસમેન્ટનો તેનો એક્સપિરિયન્સ જણાવ્યો હતો ત્યારે મને ખ્યાલ આવ્યો હતો. મને સમજાયું કે, ઓ ગોડ, વર્ષો પહેલાં મારી સાથે જે થયું હતું એ વાસ્તવમાં વર્કપ્લેસ પર સેક્સ્યુઅલ હેરેસમેન્ટ હતું. મને એનો બિલકુલ ખ્યાલ નહોતો આવ્યો. એ વ્યક્તિએ મને સ્પર્શ નહોતો કર્યો અને હું ત્યાંથી નીકળી જવામાં સફળ રહી હતી.’

કોઈનું નામ લીધા વિના સ્વરાએ કહ્યું હતું કે, ‘હેરેસમેન્ટ વર્કપ્લેસ પર થયું હતું અને એ ડિરેક્ટર ‘હવસખોર’ હતો. મને એનો ખ્યાલ આવતાં છથી આઠ વર્ષ લાગ્યા હતા. આવા પ્રકારની પેનલ ડિસ્કશનમાં બીજા કોઈએ હેરેસમેન્ટનો તેનો એક્સપિરિયન્સ જણાવ્યો હતો ત્યારે મને ખ્યાલ આવ્યો હતો. મને સમજાયું કે, ઓ ગોડ, વર્ષો પહેલાં મારી સાથે જે થયું હતું એ વાસ્તવમાં વર્કપ્લેસ પર સેક્સ્યુઅલ હેરેસમેન્ટ હતું. મને એનો બિલકુલ ખ્યાલ નહોતો આવ્યો. એ વ્યક્તિએ મને સ્પર્શ નહોતો કર્યો અને હું ત્યાંથી નીકળી જવામાં સફળ રહી હતી.’

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
happy 89th birthday to the icon that is tippi hedren! tippi starred in my favourite hitchcock movie of all time 'the birds,' and two years ago, i had the privilege to interview the icon herself for image magazine (@image.ie)! it was a true 'pinch me' moment. as a film obsessive, it remains one of the best moments in my career to date. we spoke for over 30 minutes about her life, career, work as an animal rights activist and how much she loved ireland. it could even be said that she herself was a part of #metoo before it ever officially came into being - having endured and spoken out against repeated incidents of harassment during the making of her first film. she was humble, sweet and even invited me to visit her out in her shambala preserve - something i've yet to take her up on! have a read of our chat in the link in my bio if you wish 💫 .
.
.
.
.

text:
gop is dead. gop remains dead. and we have killed him. how shall we comfort ourselves, the murderers of all murderers? what was holiest and mightiest of all that the world has yet owned has bled to death under our knives: who will wipe this blood off us? what water is there for us to clean ourselves? what festivals of atonement, what sacred games shall we have to invent? is not the greatness of this deed too great for us? must we ourselves not become gods simply to appear worthy of it?

howlindsey doody

text:
only a couple of weeks left in january. which means #humantraffickingawarenessmonth is almost over. but creating awareness does not need to end.

almost a year ago, i was looking for an internship to complete my college degree. i felt like i had applied to a hundred places. but i just wasn’t hearing anything back. i was getting discouraged.

then something almost comical happened. i was on @instagram and saw a post from @higgins.ben about a project called “project beautiful.” out of interest i clicked on the attached link and discovered @lovejusticeintl. something led me to an internship page and before i new what was happening, an application.

it wasn’t until after i’d already filled the application out and turned it in that i fully realized the scope of what i’d done. i just applied for an internship in nepal. 😱😬😶 what happened next, happened so fast. but it felt right. sure it was scary, but it was also exciting.

and so i found myself in nepal four months later. and i met these people in the above picture. and i got to walk alongside @lovejusticeintl in their mission to end human trafficking and the world’s greatest injustices.

it was a summer i will never forget. one that changed my life. more importantly, i got to see it change others lives, as beautiful girls were intercepted from becoming victims in modern day slavery. and it was seeing their lives change that really made it truly unforgettable.

if you want to be a part in changing others lives for good, in bringing justice back into the world, visit @lovejusticeintl page and click on their link in their bio.

because every life is beautiful and worth saving. and because your voice matters.
name: Ariel Shaylynn
tweet_full:
only a couple of weeks left in january. which means #humantraffickingawarenessmonth is almost over. but creating awareness does not need to end.

almost a year ago, i was looking for an internship to complete my college degree. i felt like i had applied to a hundred places. but i just wasn’t hearing anything back. i was getting discouraged.

then something almost comical happened. i was on @instagram and saw a post from @higgins.ben about a project called “project beautiful.” out of interest i clicked on the attached link and discovered @lovejusticeintl. something led me to an internship page and before i new what was happening, an application.

it wasn’t until after i’d already filled the application out and turned it in that i fully realized the scope of what i’d done. i just applied for an internship in nepal. 😱😬😶 what happened next, happened so fast. but it felt right. sure it was scary, but it was also exciting.

and so i found myself in nepal four months later. and i met these people in the above picture. and i got to walk alongside @lovejusticeintl in their mission to end human trafficking and the world’s greatest injustices.

it was a summer i will never forget. one that changed my life. more importantly, i got to see it change others lives, as beautiful girls were intercepted from becoming victims in modern day slavery. and it was seeing their lives change that really made it truly unforgettable.

if you want to be a part in changing others lives for good, in bringing justice back into the world, visit @lovejusticeintl page and click on their link in their bio.

because every life is beautiful and worth saving. and because your voice matters.

👏🏻anti-racist and pro-unity
👏🏼anti-heterosexist and anti-cisgenderist

👏🏾pro-choice and empowering all women
👏🏿fat positive and body positive

text:
how dare my government put my women in harms way. why do we keep importing these people who already hold women in low regard and see white women as "whores"? do britons rape? yes. do we want to stop rape? yes. will there always be rape? sadly yes. but why are we so held bent on adding to the problem? women are the weaker vessels, how on earth can we protect them if we keep unloading hoards and hoards of migrants onto our western nations? they have no respect towards western values - why should we further endanger our women and children? i am absolutely shocked and appalled at this weak government. i have seen so much abuse towards women in their own countries. these "refugees" are not our responsibility. thus, i could care less about them. as a gen z lad, this mass importation of the third world scares me. if you are for mass migration - every time they rape a woman - you are an accomplice and are equally responsible.
where are the feminists? no where to be seen as usual.

text:
i̇randa deputat salman xudadinin cinsi təcavüzünə məruz qalan güney azərbaycanlı qadın zəhra nəvidpurun müəmmalı ölümü ilə bağlı sosial şəbəkələrdə kampaniya başlayıb.

azenglishnews.com teleqraf.com-a istinadən xəbər verir ki, güney azərbaycandan olan qadınlar #metoo (mən də) haştağı ilə başlayan kampaniyaya qoşulublar.

kampaniyanın iştirakçısı olan qadınlar xəstəxanalar, ictimai nəqliyyat və iş yerlərində cinsi təcavüzə məruz qaldıqlarını bildiriblər.

paylaşımlar azərbaycan dilində edilir.

qeyd edək ki, 28 yaşlı zəhra nəvidpurun müəmmalı ölümündən sonra qadınların məruz qaldığı cinsi istismar və zorakılıq halları ilə bağlı məsələlər güney azərbaycanda gündəmə gəlib.

zəhra bir neçə ay əvvəl i̇ran parlamentinin deputatı salman xudadadinin ofisində onun tərəfindən təcavüzə uğradığını bildirmişdi.

57 yaşlı salman xudadadi vaxtilə i̇ran i̇nqilab keşikçiləri korpusunun (“sepah”) komandirlərindən biri olub. o, tərəfdarları arasında hacı salman adı ilə tanınır.

xatırladaq ki, məlikanın təzəqala kənd sakini zəhra nəvidpurun cansız bədəni yanvarın 6-da anasının evində tapılıb. onun qəsdən qətlə yetirildiyi iddia olunur.

#aztagram #azenglishnews

text:
the peoria heights art committee is excited to announce the return of the peoria heights fine art fair to further our growing reputation as a cultural destination in illinois.  the art fair will be held on saturday, may 11, 2019 from 9 am to 5 pm in conjunction with the 2019 more than pink walk, an event organized by susan g. komen.  our fair will be juried and feature fine artists from the region.

the peoria heights fine art fair will bring greater exposure to the many professional artists who are living and working in central illinois.  the works will be displayed in classic white tents positioned along prospect road between glen and seiberling avenues.  tower park will host food trucks, entertainment and children’s art programs. 
artists interested in signing up please click the sign up button which will take you to the zapplication site with all the details.

artfully yours
peoria heights art committee

text:
یادداشتی درباره ی آنلاین استاکینگ (مزاحمت مجازی)

فرض کنید در اتاق دو متر در دو متری حبس شده اید و محکومید به زندگی. روی میز تحریر نشسته اید و کتاب میخوانید و ویز ویز اعصاب خردکن و مزاحم پشه ای هرازگاهی شما را می رنجاند. آن را پس می زنید و متمرکز می مانید. فضا بسته است و پنجره ای نیست و ویز ویز و پشه مرتبن به سمت شما بازمیگردند. چه میکنید؟ یک ساعت و دو ساعت و هشت ساعت که بگذرد ؛ یا واقعن عادت مکینید و می سازید و یا نهایتن دستهایتان را باز می کنید و با یک دست زدنِ سریع پشه را له میکنید و بعد دستتان را تمیز میکنید. جدای این دو ، انتخاب دیگری هم هست؟
داستان من و خیلی آدمهای دیگر درباره ی مزاحمتهای مجازی شاید چیزی در همین حدود باشد. به اندازه ی کافی صدای مزاحم را پس زده و ندیده گرفته ایم ؛ شاید در حد چند دقیقه اعصابمان از حماقت یا بهتر بگویم وقاحت بعضی از کاربرهای مجازی بهم خورده ؛ اما برای من حالا زمان مکتوب کردنِ مختصرِ واکنش است ؛ چون از "عادت به چیزی که نباید باشد" بیزارم.
دو نوع مواجهه وجود دارد وقتی کاربری بدون داشتن سوال خاصی درباره ی مطلب خاصی که نوشته اید به شما "پیغام خصوصی میدهد: یا مایل به آشنایی است (حالا از نوع آشنایی دو انسان و یا آشنایی ای که در دایره ی واژگان فارسی اسمش را "لاس زدن" می گذاریم.) ، و یا مزاحم است. تفاوت بین این دو؟ گاهی بقدر مویی باریک است. اگر حکم کلی بدهیم(بخوانید جاج کردن و آنوقت نچ نچ کنان سرتان را از راست به چپ و چپ به راست بچرخانید) ، وقتی شما به نوعی نشان می دهید مایل به ادامه یا اصلن شروع گفتگو نیستید و همچنان کاربرمورد نظر شما را تحت فشارِ پیام های بی سرو ته و عبث می گذارد ؛ این یعنی مزاحمت.
دو دلیل احتمالی که به ذهن من میرسد ؛ فرض بر اینکه مخاطب من فقط کاربران ایرانی باشند ؛ این است :
یک. طبق تجربه ی کاربر مذکور ، دختران ایرانی با نه گفتن ، منظورشان حقیقتن "نه" نیست ، بلکه شروع بازی ای است که با "دست پس زدن و با پا پیش کشیدن" در فرهنگمان توصیفش میکنیم.
دو. چون پیام "خصوصی" است و مردم نمی بینند ، اصرار مُجاز است. تجاوز به حریم ، وقت ، اعصاب و یا اصلن نخواستن یک نفر ، که فعلن فقط عکس پروفایلی است در یک اپلیکیشن 
موبایل ، مجاز است و اشکالی ندارد.
طبق تجربه ی من ، تعداد زیادی از این افراد که مزاحمان مجازی صدایشان میزنم ، اگر تخفیف بدهم و نخواهم بی اغراق از لفط "متجاوز" استفاده کنم،*ادامه در كامنت اول*

این دو؟ گاهی بقدر مویی باریک است . اگر حکم کلی بدهیم ( بخوانید جاج کردن و آنوقت نچ نچ کنان سرتان را از راست به چپ و چپ به راست بچرخانید ) ، وقتی شما به نوعی نشان می دهید مایل به ادامه یا اصلن شروع گفتگو نیستید و همچنان کاربرمورد نظر شما را تحت فشارِ پیام های بی سرو ته و عبث می گذارد ؛ این یعنی مزاحمت . دو دلیل احتمالی که به ذهن من میرسد ؛ فرض بر اینکه مخاطب من فقط کاربران ایرانی باشند ؛ این است : یک . طبق تجربه ی کاربر مذکور ، دختران ایرانی با نه گفتن ، منظورشان حقیقتن `` نه '' نیست ، بلکه شروع بازی ای است که با `` دست پس زدن و با پا پیش کشیدن '' در فرهنگمان توصیفش میکنیم . دو . چون پیام `` خصوصی '' است و مردم نمی بینند ، اصرار مُجاز است . تجاوز به حریم ، وقت ، اعصاب و یا اصلن نخواستن یک نفر ، که فعلن فقط عکس پروفایلی است در یک اپلیکیشن موبایل ، مجاز است و اشکالی ندارد . طبق تجربه ی من ، تعداد زیادی از این افراد که مزاحمان مجازی صدایشان میزنم ، اگر تخفیف بدهم و نخواهم بی اغراق از لفط `` متجاوز '' استفاده کنم،*ادامه در كامنت اول*

text:
power cycle saturday’s are back with my crew!
.
man i’ve missed this class the past month! a bunch of dedicated, hardcore badasses all showed up after driving through a freaking blizzard this morning to get to class! ☃️🌬❄️
.
there was a moment this am i thought it would be easier to stay home and ride my trainer than to drag my kids and myself through the snowy/icy roads and chiberia snowstorm before the sun was even up ...
but!!!!!
.
i knew my teacher would show up and i knew my 87 year old training partner and legend bob scott would show up with zero bullshit excuses about it being too cold or snowy. 😂
.
and to make it even better bob told me he had been up since 1am not only shoveling his driveway but all his neighbors! he always shovels everyone’s driveway/walkway (yes at 87!) but today he thought he’d get started early at 1am 😂🙈
.
so yah....if you’re thinking whether you should train today or not ... remember bob has been shoveling snow, got his 2 hour cycling in and is back shoveling snow as we speak at 87 years old 🔥💪🏽👊🏽 #myfreakinghero ❤️🥰
.
here was our class today:
wu
20 min z2
15 min z3
10 min top of z3
5 min z4
3 min z5
3 min z5
4 min build to 110% ftp
cd
.
sooooooooo excited to be back in saddle and get training for #ironmanchattanooga again! 🚴🏻‍♀️👊🏽💥
#ironmantraining #ironwoman #thistimeitspersonal 😈 #metoo #veganathlete #vegantriathlete 🌱

text:
in our community everyday, acts of violence and direct and indirect trauma happen daily if not hourly. many are fighting for change through policy, advocacy, and often support but are we addressing the trauma itself? are we ever processing the trauma? are we talking to our children about their experiences? are we using these moments as teachable moments? are we seeking counseling or therapy or are we perpetuating the cycle of violence by shoving down our experiences, passing blame and outright ignoring the pain we are in? i challenge all of us to unpack our trauma and teach another until we all are healed from our wounds and see our communities as safe havens! what are your ideas on changing how we address violence and trauma? 👑✨💕💎
.

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: lately i’ve been getting a lot of questions like: “how can i be happy like you?” or “how can i be calm like you?” the thing is, as much joy that i was able to bring others in the past, i wasn’t able to give that to myself. i’ve had my #metoo moments, a myriad of eating disorders, post partum came later for me when i stopped breastfeeding, serious of unfortunate events, drank and ate too much and i lived toooo fast. the only thing that has been healing and able to take me to the next level has been slowing down and tuning into what i really want and need. i stopped doing what i was “supposed to do” and started doing things every day that make me happy. these things include eating beautiful plant based foods, drinking tea, gathering with friends to play music, dance, practice yoga and spend a lot more time at home. so, my advice to be calmer and happier is to slow down even if you don’t have the luxury to be home all the time. you don’t have to rush, take a few minutes a day to breathe and find things you really love and do them every day. 📸 @delaheart_ #mamattribe #slowdown #happiness #calm #goodvibesonly

text:
how i basically feel about the #gillettead:
🧑
"but on social media, one man called it 'a condescending ad from a company that relies on men buying their products.' another wrote that 'being a man is not a disease nor a pathology,' adding that 'it is grotesque to repeatedly ascribe collective guilt onto half of humanity known as men.'"
🧑🏻
like "how dare you market products to us and ask us to exhibit human decency?" 😂
👨🏿
this sounds like #notallmen or what people of a certain hue say when they hear words like "white privilege" and "white supremacy." #alllivesmatter
🧑🏼
reminds me of when people boycotted nike and #colinkaepernick by cutting out the check mark/swoosh from their clothes.
🧑🏽
newsflash: nike and @gillette already have your money (but if you insist on being a fool, please dispose of your razors safely).
🧑🏾
it saddens me deeply that people are more upset at being told to be morally decent than they are about #racism and #toxicmasculinity. it bothers me that this ad is seen as divisive -- and not by just a few people on the fringe.
🧑🏿
if you are offended when an ad or campaign challenges your privilege, ask yourself, "why?"
👨
no one is saying that there is anything wrong with being a man -- unless you define masculinity as denigrating others. then it's problematic. you may not ascribe to toxic masculinity but you do benefit from patriarchy and #maleprivilege. and if you do not *actively* do your part to question your privilege, dismantle toxic masculinity and use your privilege to protect and promote the voices of the vulnerable other, you are part of the problem. you are complicit. silence is complicity. be offended.
👨🏻
so this ad basically says what we've been saying since time immemorial and definitely since #metoo: #dobetter.
👨🏼
we only ask that men do better because we know that they can. you have the potential to be better men.

text: tonight as sat in my rocking chair i found myself holding a few crystals in my hands and i was rubbing my hands cupped together in a motion that simulated "warming them up" and i became aware that, i didn't send any type of thought that "i want to rub my hands together with these crystals (which asked me to pick them up a few minutes before) in the direction i was rubbing". what was happening was completely on its own and i did not ask this to happen. so at a conscious level i asked myself "what does this mean", so i focused my attention into my hands and i could feel the warmth that was being generated but i knew that my hands are moving far too slow to be generating this warmth, so i focused on the warmth and when i did this, in an instance i had a vision which lasted a nano second but long enough to know that just happened, so i let go of trying to figure out what i just saw and it appeared again only this time it lasted longer, the vision was long enough to see what resembles a fracture in my physical vision, i saw the room in front of me, all that i was looking at split and as i remained in the lower portion of the split (there was 3 splits) the middle portion of the screen transformed itself from representing something that was my living room/ kitchen and became something different, it was like something was being injected into this potion of the video steam, like a movie, and the new "video stream" showed an entirely different reality, and each time the new vision updated itself the more i could see into that reality, what i saw first were hands rubbing themselves together with crystals in their hands, white hands, glowing a shade of "white" that was the color of love, it was warm and the light surrounded  the hands, pulsing, and the first thing i felt was wisdom beyond truth, ancient, aged, soft and when i looked down the hands towards the finger tips out from the finger tips projected light beams all moving forward, i saw it as individual projections of realities, and as the hands continued to move in a slow rotating warming motion the images continued to project from the hand through the finger tips. i will post more of this vision shortly :)

text:
so if i haven’t seen this recently, gillette, a mens hygiene company, has dropped a new add (clearly a publicity stunt) i can see people dont like this video, whether for trying to tackle the #metoo movement or the trying to tackle childhood bullying. they are right. “boys will be boys” thats simple male biology, male humans are more aggressive and dominated, we cant take away rough housing cause that takes away much needed energy loss. but at the same time we cant ignore bullying, men cant just roam free as ignorant dicks but simply need to control their behaviors. and with sexual assault or harassment or putting a women in a uncomfortable situation, we do need to do better, i personally have friends that ik that have been on both ends of the spectrum of sexual assault. ik teachers that have used their position, guys and girls who take advantage of their partners and using them for pleasure. ik people who’ve been assaulted, raped, harassed. ik people are upset that this video makes it seem like all men are animals but you can see in the ad there a men tho stop these acts, from something as simple as cat-calling, or stopping a kid from getting beaten up. our society isnt about personal lessons anymore, yet about a tv culture where we learn from what we watch. hell even the porn u watch can change the way you act. we need people to act hard on this issue cause its a very personal that i and many others have to experience. i like this ad. it may be a little corny or ignorant but it has the right message. we as a society need to do better and thats the bottom line.
#gillette #powerinnumbers #metoo #metoomovement

text: @teddy_quinlivan summarising the issues facing the modelling industry perfectly in the latest @modelsdot interview. ‘i don’t think any industry is too riddled with problems; it’s just i can’t change it all myself, i can’t be the only one coming out and saying, “this isn’t acceptable, this isn’t okay.” it’s gonna take more than one model, it’s gonna take more than 10 models, it’s gonna take more than 100 models. it’s gonna take all of us coming together and demanding human rights and demanding that we are treated well and treated fairly and paid well. that won’t happen until we all collectively come together and ask for more and until the people in power, the big agencies, the casting directors, the stylists and the executives all understand that we need to be treated better, as well. it’s more than just creating a charter. it’s more than just creating a fancy piece of paper that has rules written on it. there needs to be some kind of tangible, enforceable aspect to these protections and guidelines. it has to be more than a nutrition chart. it has to be enforced in one way or another. i think getting people to check themselves is very difficult. i think we also live in a culture and time where people are really, really, really terrified because they’re scared something’s going to come out about them or that they didn’t treat everybody in their career very well and we point the finger at one person and then they say, “well, what about this person? and they did this, too. and that’s horrible.” it’s like, okay, we need to stop pointing the finger at people and we need to just point the finger at the industry, collectively and say, “what can we do to be better?” what can we do to be better because it’s such a progressive industry and we’re setting the tone for what’s aspirational and what’s acceptable and what’s in style and what’s in fashion and what’s cool.’ stand up for your rights and make a practical change with @themodelmanifesto 🙌🏽

lissage coréen par top beauty tendances à partir de 150€

le lissage coréen, c’est quoi?
petit frère du lissage japonais, le lissage coréen change la structure du cheveu pour la raidir de manière permanente.
le principe du lissage coréen
ce lissage ne nourrit pas le cheveu, mais modifie sa nature pour le raidir en douceur.
il change sa structure en rendant le cheveux raide manière définitive.
il peut être effectué sur les cheveux traités ou colorés.
quelle différence avec le lissage japonais ?
le lissage coréen est légèrement moins lissant que le japonais. pour un résultat impeccablement raide, on choisira donc plutôt ce dernier.
« tout comme le coréen, le lissage japonais détend la fibre du cheveu de manière douce.
en moyenne, il est donc conseillé de le faire deux fois par an

pour qui ?
le lissage coréen est conseillé aux cheveux naturels ou colorés/mèches.

text:
lissage japonais par top beauty tendances à partir de 185€

coiffeuse diplômée et professionnelle je vous propose le lissage japonais, un lissage qui vous permettra d'avoir une chevelure raide et cela définitivement.
entre 6 et 8 mois vous n aurez que les repousses à traiter.
vos questions et toutes nos réponses sur le lissage japonais :
la coloration ne constitue pas une incompatibilité au lissage japonais il faut la réaliser – minimum – 7 jours auparavant. indiquez le tout de même.
lissage japonais s’adapte-t-il aux cheveux méchés /oxydés ?
les cheveux méchés ont subi une oxydation (différents degrés d’oxydation). lorsque celle-ci est pratiquée dans une certaine mesure, le lissage peut être effectué avec un traitement préalable qui va égaliser la porosité. dans le cas d’oxydation trop importante, la procédure ne peut être réalisée qu’après des soins. seul un professionnel peut estimer ce degré.
peut-on faire des mèches après lissage japonais ?
oui, après un délai de 4 semaines permettant la stabilisation.
lissage japonais peut-il être effectué après un défrisage ?
les défrisages ainsi que lissage japonais sont incompatibles
lissage japonais peut-il être réalisé en cas de grossesse ?
lors de cette période, il se peut que le cheveu se révèle plus résistant et altère l’action de lissage japonais qui peut moins bien fonctionner. cette particularité peut cependant varier d’une femme à l’autre.
lissage japonais peut-il être réalisé sur des enfants ?
lissage japonais ne comporte aucun risque. l’enfance et l’adolescence sont des périodes pendant lesquelles un certain nombre d’hormones sont produites et la forme définitive du cheveu n’est pas encore atteinte.
peut-on utiliser un shampoing usuel ?
il est aussi déconseillé d’utiliser des shampoings contenant de l’hydroxyde de sodium.

“every injustice and human rights violation that women face in this world — from rape to domestic violence to female genital mutilation to child marriages to sexual assault — stems from the belief that women are lesser beings than men. that women are the weaker partner in marriage and husbands have authority over their wives. that women should be “saved” for marriage and a woman’s “value” is rooted in her virginity. that women are second-class citizens not entitled to positions of power or authority. that women are the source of sin and temptation. that they are responsible for suppressing men’s sexual urges by dressing and acting modestly. that they were designed to fulfill their husbands’ sexual desires and give them offspring. that childbirth and periods are curses. all of these beliefs have permeated the airwaves in societies all over the world for centuries and have played a role in the global disenfranchisement and abuse of women and girls.”

text:
manjima mohan on #metoo: some allegations are believable and some are not believable
#
manjima mohan, who is known for her tamil and malayalam films, has opened up about #metoo movement. the actress said that she has not faced any such instances in her career. manjima mohanmanjima mohan, who made her tamil debut in gautham menon's achcham yenbathu madamaiyada, went on to act in few handfuls of films like sathriyan and ipadai vellum. now, the actress is part of zam zam and devarattam.according to a tamil daily, the actress has opened up about the #metoo movement, which has called out many leading celebs of indian cinema.manjima was quoted as saying, "some allegations are believable and some allegations are not believable. but when you hear them, it makes your blood boil."the actress said that she has never faced any kind of sexual harassment in the film industry, and has never heard (first-person account) about such instances.in tamil, lyricist vairamuthu, director susi ganesan and actor radha ravi faced allegations of sexual harassment.manjima will next be seen in malayalam remake of hindi blockbuster queen. the film is titled zam zam.also read| chinmayi sripaada: kept distance from vairamuthu after he asked me to 'cooperate'also watch | benny dayal and chinmayi sripada on working with ar rahmanget real-time alerts…

text:
privileged:

straight, white, middle class male, privileged,
sat well fed & clothed, lounging in the house i own,
books & magazines are everywhere in my home,
to read is to learn but also to live a life not your own,
so, i feast on history, news & novels as if starved,
knowing the only hunger i’ve ever felt in my life is to know more,
and i read with righteous anger at society’s many wrongs,
for every emancipation there’s segregation, too much degradation,
it’s clear every damn battle for equality has shed too much blood,
or so it seems, sat in my conservatory, rolex on my wrist,
i look at my wife with deep love & warm glowing pride,
not a possession or bauble but a strong, independent woman,
but it burns me to think of the prejudices she’s faced,
just for being a woman even in this day & age,
#metoo, #timesup, #blacklivesmatter shows how far still we have to go,
no ‘whites only’ buses & bars anymore but racism lurks,
my pale, white skin spots red with anger when i think this,
i try looking for positives, focus on the good, try to be a better man,
then worry i’m mansplaining when i explain why this matters,
the fragile male ego assuming my words count or carry weight,
am i so arrogant that i think my thoughts will make a difference,
domestic violence, corruption, racism, sexism, ageism, just being a dick,
all cured by the strokes of my montblanc pen on smythson paper,
if i’m being honest the truth is i’m scared about what i am,
could it be i’m an ignorant bigot with too many silk ties, too many words?
that my cosseted upbringing makes it easy to hide in plain sight,
that if this was sixty years ago i’d be living a very different life,
an alcoholic, wife beating, whites only, arrogant suited prick,
concerned only with the fold of my pocket square or next cocktail,
this is a hypothetical argument that seems impossible to resolve,
so instead of bleating on i should just take a simple step,
believe that i’m inherently good, that it’s not a privileged illusion,
like quitting the booze, just take it one step & day at a time,
continue being a good son, husband, friend & colleague,
and if this was sixty years ago, know i’d still feel the same way.

mark dilnot - jan 19

text:
the auditorium was filled with overflowing interest and attention when the keynote speaker, professor salome martinez salazar, took over the stage and presented layers and details of her life experiences as a mathematician and a woman in her workspace, in a male-dominated field of study. ‘environment and changing gender equations’, was the theme of the keynote address. the lack of women professionals in her department, minimum women representation in stem education, significant wage gap, the #metoo movement, were some of the topics of her discussion , with respect to the state of chile universities and the challenges faced by the country. she pointed towards a change in priorities; towards improved protocols for harassment/ abuse cases, and non-sexist education. 
bringing an end to the inaugural session, ms. shama mitra chenoy addressed the audience with a vote of thanks and an expression of gratitude. 
with a short break, session i: women and health progressed. ms. aparna jain felicitated and introduced the speakers for the session. 
dr. ramesh awasthi, co-convenor and managing trustee, m a s u m, the first speaker of the session, talked about factors affecting women’s health; systematic failures in the form of poverty, poor environmental hygiene; absence of women’s rights on their own bodies; and abortion rights.
dr. nupur kohli, advisor-health advisory services at ey, netherlands, shared her presentation with a discussion on who facts on women and health. the significance of women health, be it physical or mental, was greatly emphasized. 
professor rama v. baru, jnu university, pointed her concern towards anemia in women. some important areas defining women’s health such as reproductive health, increase in bio-medicalization; along with the minimization of women health to mere risks were brought to light. 
the platform given to various major topics on women health left an ever-lasting impression on the audience, allowing them to have a better and informed outlook. 
ms. aparna jain, concluded the session, with a vote of thanks.
name: WDC,Shivaji College

‘대전 a여고’의 졸업생으로 대전스쿨미투대전공동대책위원회에 참여하며 느낀점을 적었습니다. 19년에는 학교 안의 여학생들이 더 안전할 수 있길 바라며.
올해도 우리 모두가 #스쿨미투 에 더 많은 관심을 가질 수 있다면 좋겠습니다.
_
보슈의 권사랑 대표가 대전여민회 회지에 기고한 글입니다. 사진을 넘기시면 대전스쿨미투공대위의 글도 확인하실 수 있어요.

text:
trigger warning: death
my sibling was murdered at a very young age. not by any random strangers. but our very own relatives. my dad was the bread earner of the family since a very young age. so obviously he'd been providing them money and everything. when he got married and had a child, they were worried that my father won't give them as much money as before or will stop giving because now he has a child to look after. so they killed the child. it's been ages. and to this day they are still living well. karma didn't hit them. i don't wish any bad for them but they deserve the karma to hit them. and to this day i wonder how different my life would have been if i had an elder figure in my life. how different, how amazing, i can only wonder.
•

text:
tuko busy sana - tunawaachia nani watoto wetu

hii clip imenikumbusha jinsi tunavyo wategemea sana wadada wa kazi kuwaangalia watoto wetu.

kuna mtoto mmoja wa miaka 9 alikua analala chumba kimoja na dada wa kazi. huyu dada wa kazi alipewa pesa na mkaka mmoja ili usiku awe anamfungulia mlango mkubwa wa nyumba na kumpeleka chumbani kwao ili awe anamwingia huyu mtoto. kwa kipindi kirefu sana huyu jmakak alikuwa anafanya hiki kitendo cha kinyama huku dada akiwa amekaa pembeni ameshikilia kisu kumtishia ymtoto akipiga kelele atamwua na kile kisu.

sasa shuleni mwalimu aliona jinsi mtoto anavyosinzia darasani, homework hafanyi na akifanya hafanyi vizuri, alikua ana pungua uzito na alikuwa mnyonge sana, akimwandika mzazi majibu anayoyapata hayaeleweki. kube ni dada wa kazi ndio alipewa jukumu la kumshughulikia huyu mtoto kunzia kwnda shule, kufanya nae homework, kuwasiliana na walimu. huyu mwalimu alimfuatilia sana na kumwuliza maswali menti mtoto lakini alikuwa anakataa kusema ukweli shauri alikua anaogopa kuchomwa kisu. huyu mwalimu alimfanya huyu mtoto awe rafiki yake paka mtoto akamwamini na kumweleza kila kitu. mwalimu alivyosikia alilia sana na kumtafuta mzazi. 
mama hakupatikana ila baba aliweza kuja shule. baba alipokuja shule na kusikia majanga yaliyomtokea mtoto wake alizimia. cha kusikitisha sana, mtoto alipopimwa ukimwi akukutwa ameathirika

tunajifunza nini

1. tusiwaamini sana wadada wa kazi

2. ongea na mtoto kila siku hata kama uko busy vipi - mpigie simu, jua yuko wapi na anafanya nini

3. mjue na kuwa na mahusiano mazuri na mwalimu wa mwanao

4. iwapo mtoto anakataa kwenda nyumba fulani, na akimwona mtu fulani anashtuka/anakaa mbali nae...msikilize na mwulize kwanini

5. hata kama wanalala wa mwisho na kuamka wa kwanza, tusiwaachie dada funguo za nyumba. wanaweza kuleta hata majambazi pia.
.
.

text:
unsere erste uraufführung im neuen jahr steht heute an. 🤩
.
wir wünschen regisseurin babett grube und ihrem gesamten team auf, hinter und vor der bühne herzlichst toi! toi! toi! für ihre inszenierung mit freundlichen grüssen eure pandora von laura naumann 19.30 uhr im kleinen haus 2.
.
die uraufführung ist breits ausverkauft. eventuelle restkarten können ab 18.30 uhr an der abendkasse erfragt werden.
wer mit uns feiern möchte, kommt vorbei, die premierenfeier findet im foyer und im bistro klara des kleinen hauses statt, dj danzel legt für euch auf. der eintritt dazu ist frei.
.
nächste vorstellungen: 26.01.*, 02.02. und 12.02.2019, jeweils 19.30 uhr
*blauer tag! alle plätze 10,00 €
.
karten und informationen: bit.ly/ssdd_pandora
.
fotos: sebastian hoppe
.

name: Télérama
pre_proc_tweet:
glenn close par platon. l'hiver des récompenses, à hollywood, c’est la saison des larmes. tout lauréat verse la sienne. on se croyait blasés. et pouant, le 6 janvier, glenn close aurait ému un caillou. en recevant un golden globe pour sa prestation dans the wife, de björn runge, la comédienne de 71 ans a même réussi à faire pleurer ses concurrentes, de lady ­gaga à nicole kidman. « nous devrions toutes être ici, sur scène », leur a-t-elle lancé. toutes les actrices, et toutes les femmes. dans son bref discours, qui depuis tourne en boucle dans le monde entier, elle les a soudain rassemblées. honorées. ses cadettes qui luttent pour leurs droits, dans une ­industrie dominée par les hommes, mais aussi sa propre mère qui s’est « sublimée toute sa vie »pour son mari. et même cette épouse d’écrivain qu’elle vient d’interpréter dans the wife : ­sacrifiée volontaire, « faiseuse de roi », comme il est dit dans le film. nombreuses sont celles qui, de podiums en micros, ont paagé cette ferveur féministe dans les remous de l’ère post-etoo.
mais ce soir-là, glenn close y a appoé son supplément d’âme. une puissance douce dans ses traits volontaires, presque durs, si familiers des écrans depuis quarante-cinq ans. les fantômes de tous ses personnages, dans une carrière qui raconte, à sa ­manière, une histoire de la lutte des genres. à lire dans télérama et telerama.fr le porait "coup de poing" de cécile mury. ©platon/trunk archive/photosenso     hewifemovie

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the effos made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to cou documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

michelle nichols
reuters
